1
00:00:10,303 --> 00:00:15,803
<i>[THE GODFATHER THEME PLAYING]</i>

2
00:00:51,324 --> 00:00:54,197
BONASERA: I believe in America.

3
00:00:54,240 --> 00:00:57,287
America has made my fortune.

4
00:00:57,330 --> 00:01:01,465
And I raised my daughter
in the American fashion.

5
00:01:01,508 --> 00:01:06,383
I gave her freedom, but I taught
her never to dishonor her family.

6
00:01:07,776 --> 00:01:10,996
She found a boyfriend,
not an Italian.

7
00:01:11,040 --> 00:01:13,085
She went to the movies
with him.

8
00:01:13,129 --> 00:01:15,522
She stayed out late.

9
00:01:15,566 --> 00:01:18,308
I didn't protest.

10
00:01:18,351 --> 00:01:23,052
Two months ago he took her for
a drive with another boyfriend.

11
00:01:24,009 --> 00:01:26,795
They made her drink whiskey

12
00:01:26,838 --> 00:01:31,234
and then they tried to
take advantage of her.

13
00:01:31,277 --> 00:01:35,412
She resisted,
she kept her honor.

14
00:01:36,630 --> 00:01:39,721
So they beat her
like an animal.

15
00:01:41,592 --> 00:01:46,640
When I went to the hospital,
her nose was broken,

16
00:01:46,684 --> 00:01:51,080
her jaw was shattered,
held together by wire.

17
00:01:53,256 --> 00:01:56,694
She couldn't even weep
because of the pain.

18
00:01:58,740 --> 00:02:02,221
But I wept.
Why did I weep?

19
00:02:04,920 --> 00:02:07,270
She was the light
of my life.

20
00:02:09,228 --> 00:02:10,926
Beautiful girl.

21
00:02:14,668 --> 00:02:17,454
Now she will never be
beautiful again.

22
00:02:21,284 --> 00:02:22,285
[COUGHS]

23
00:02:24,069 --> 00:02:25,505
Sorry.

24
00:02:33,862 --> 00:02:38,431
I went to the police,
like a good American.

25
00:02:38,475 --> 00:02:42,305
These two boys
were brought to trial.

26
00:02:42,348 --> 00:02:45,134
The judge sentenced them
to three years in prison,

27
00:02:45,177 --> 00:02:47,310
but suspended
the sentence.

28
00:02:48,485 --> 00:02:50,835
Suspended the sentence!

29
00:02:50,879 --> 00:02:53,577
They went free
that very day!

30
00:02:55,840 --> 00:02:59,148
I stood in the courtroom
like a fool.

31
00:02:59,191 --> 00:03:02,673
And those two bastards,
they smiled at me.

32
00:03:03,892 --> 00:03:05,371
Then I said to my wife,

33
00:03:05,415 --> 00:03:09,462
"For justice,
we must go to Don Corleone."

34
00:03:14,903 --> 00:03:16,339
VITO: Why did you
go to the police?

35
00:03:16,382 --> 00:03:18,515
Why didn't you
come to me first?

36
00:03:19,429 --> 00:03:21,039
What do you want of me?

37
00:03:21,083 --> 00:03:25,522
Tell me anything,
but do what I beg you to do.

38
00:03:25,565 --> 00:03:27,219
What is that?

39
00:03:38,404 --> 00:03:40,232
[WHISPERING]
I want them dead.

40
00:03:51,722 --> 00:03:53,028
That I cannot do.

41
00:03:54,986 --> 00:03:57,467
I'll give you
anything you ask.

42
00:03:59,817 --> 00:04:01,645
We've known each
other many years,

43
00:04:01,688 --> 00:04:06,389
but this is the first time you ever
came to me for counsel, for help.

44
00:04:06,432 --> 00:04:08,870
I can't remember
the last time that

45
00:04:08,913 --> 00:04:12,699
you invited me to your house
for a cup of coffee.

46
00:04:12,743 --> 00:04:16,573
Even though my wife is
godmother to your only child.

47
00:04:16,616 --> 00:04:18,618
But let's be frank here.

48
00:04:18,662 --> 00:04:21,665
You never wanted
my friendship.

49
00:04:21,708 --> 00:04:25,495
And you were afraid
to be in my debt.

50
00:04:25,538 --> 00:04:27,932
BONASERA: I didn't want
to get into trouble.

51
00:04:29,151 --> 00:04:30,717
I understand.

52
00:04:32,241 --> 00:04:35,113
You found Paradise
in America.

53
00:04:37,333 --> 00:04:39,248
You had a good trade,
made a good living,

54
00:04:39,291 --> 00:04:42,164
Police protected you
and there were courts of law.

55
00:04:42,207 --> 00:04:44,035
You didn't need
a friend like me.

56
00:04:46,472 --> 00:04:50,085
But now you come
to me and you say,

57
00:04:50,128 --> 00:04:52,565
"Don Corleone,
give me justice."

58
00:04:54,480 --> 00:04:57,440
But you don't ask
with respect.

59
00:04:57,483 --> 00:05:03,881
You don't offer friendship. You
don't even think to call me Godfather.

60
00:05:03,925 --> 00:05:07,363
You said you'd come into my house on
the day my daughter is to be married

61
00:05:07,406 --> 00:05:10,801
and ask me to do
murder for money.

62
00:05:10,844 --> 00:05:13,412
BONASERA:
I ask you for justice.

63
00:05:13,456 --> 00:05:16,111
That is not justice.
Your daughter is still alive.

64
00:05:17,416 --> 00:05:20,942
Let them suffer, then,
as she suffers.

65
00:05:22,813 --> 00:05:23,945
How much shall I pay you?

66
00:05:31,300 --> 00:05:32,649
[CAT MEOWS]

67
00:05:39,961 --> 00:05:43,921
Bonasera, Bonasera.

68
00:05:43,965 --> 00:05:48,143
What have I ever done to make
you treat me so disrespectfully?

69
00:05:49,274 --> 00:05:51,885
If you'd come to me
in friendship,

70
00:05:51,929 --> 00:05:57,413
then the scum that ruined your daughter
would be suffering this very day.

71
00:05:57,456 --> 00:05:59,806
And if by chance,
an honest man like yourself

72
00:05:59,850 --> 00:06:02,592
should make enemies,
then they would become my enemies.

73
00:06:05,551 --> 00:06:08,206
And then they
would fear you.

74
00:06:11,644 --> 00:06:12,732
Be my friend?

75
00:06:17,607 --> 00:06:18,695
Godfather?

76
00:06:23,874 --> 00:06:25,006
Good.

77
00:06:27,182 --> 00:06:29,488
Some day, and that day
may never come,

78
00:06:29,532 --> 00:06:32,317
I'll call upon you
to do a service for me.

79
00:06:33,666 --> 00:06:37,583
But, uh... until that day

80
00:06:37,627 --> 00:06:41,935
accept this justice as a gift
on my daughter's wedding day.

81
00:06:41,979 --> 00:06:43,285
Grazie, Godfather.

82
00:06:43,328 --> 00:06:44,547
Prego.

83
00:06:44,590 --> 00:06:45,939
[PEOPLE CHATTERING OUTSIDE]

84
00:06:51,510 --> 00:06:54,165
Give this to Clemenza.

85
00:06:56,515 --> 00:07:00,171
I want reliable people that
aren't going to be carried away.

86
00:07:00,215 --> 00:07:05,394
We were not murderers,
in spite of what this undertaker says.

87
00:07:05,437 --> 00:07:07,657
[BAND PLAYING
TRADITIONAL ITALIAN MUSIC]

88
00:07:13,445 --> 00:07:15,273
[PEOPLE CHATTERING]

89
00:07:29,505 --> 00:07:30,810
Where's Michael?

90
00:07:30,854 --> 00:07:34,031
Don't worry,
it's early

91
00:07:34,075 --> 00:07:37,208
We're not taking the picture
without Michael.

92
00:07:37,252 --> 00:07:39,080
[SPEAKING ITALIAN]

93
00:07:43,475 --> 00:07:44,563
What's the matter?

94
00:07:44,607 --> 00:07:45,912
It's Michael.

95
00:08:18,641 --> 00:08:20,425
[ALL CHEERING]

96
00:08:35,658 --> 00:08:37,138
VITO: Don Barzini.

97
00:08:40,793 --> 00:08:42,230
[VITO SPEAKING ITALIAN]

98
00:08:53,806 --> 00:08:56,983
Hey, Paulie!
Let me have some wine.

99
00:08:57,027 --> 00:08:59,377
Paulie! More wine.

100
00:08:59,421 --> 00:09:01,118
Music plays.

101
00:09:01,162 --> 00:09:02,859
Ah, you look terrific
on the floor.

102
00:09:02,902 --> 00:09:04,600
What, you a dance
judge or something?

103
00:09:04,643 --> 00:09:06,384
[SPEAKING ITALIAN]

104
00:09:06,428 --> 00:09:07,690
Go take a walk around
the neighborhood.

105
00:09:07,733 --> 00:09:08,778
Do your job.

106
00:09:14,392 --> 00:09:16,438
[MUSIC STOPS]

107
00:09:16,481 --> 00:09:18,091
Hey Sandra, come on, do me a favor.
Watch the kids.

108
00:09:18,135 --> 00:09:19,745
Don't let them run wild,
all right?

109
00:09:19,789 --> 00:09:22,183
Well, you watch
yourself, all right?

110
00:09:23,488 --> 00:09:24,968
[BAND PLAYING MAZURKA]

111
00:09:43,552 --> 00:09:47,773
20, 30 grand.
In small bills, cash.

112
00:09:48,600 --> 00:09:51,081
In that little silk purse.

113
00:09:51,124 --> 00:09:54,693
If this were somebody else's wedding...
Sfortunato!

114
00:09:54,737 --> 00:09:56,042
Hey, Paulie!

115
00:09:56,086 --> 00:09:59,872
I got two gabagool,
capocol, and a prosciut.

116
00:09:59,916 --> 00:10:01,091
PAULIE: Stupid jerk!

117
00:10:10,143 --> 00:10:12,102
Hey, what's the matter?

118
00:10:24,332 --> 00:10:25,768
Have to go back to work.

119
00:10:25,811 --> 00:10:27,813
Oh, Tom.
It's part of the wedding.

120
00:10:27,857 --> 00:10:31,252
No Sicilian can refuse any request
on his daughter's wedding day.

121
00:10:34,733 --> 00:10:36,953
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

122
00:10:36,996 --> 00:10:42,088
Don Corleone, I am honored and grateful
that you have invited me to your home.

123
00:10:44,700 --> 00:10:46,397
Hey!

124
00:10:46,441 --> 00:10:47,703
Partire. Get out of here!

125
00:10:47,746 --> 00:10:50,140
It's a private party.
Go on!

126
00:10:50,923 --> 00:10:52,142
What is it?

127
00:10:52,185 --> 00:10:54,231
Hey, it's my sister's wedding.

128
00:11:00,672 --> 00:11:03,458
SONNY: Goddamn FBI
don't respect nothing!

129
00:11:06,504 --> 00:11:09,899
Hey! Come here, come here,
come here, come here!

130
00:11:24,174 --> 00:11:28,787
...but towards the end, he was paroled
to help with the American war effort,

131
00:11:28,831 --> 00:11:31,921
so for the last six months he's
been working in my pastry shop.

132
00:11:31,964 --> 00:11:34,619
Nazorine, my friend,
What can I do for you?

133
00:11:34,663 --> 00:11:36,752
Now that
the war is over,

134
00:11:36,795 --> 00:11:40,886
this boy, Enzo, they want to
repatriate him back to Italy.

135
00:11:40,930 --> 00:11:43,367
Godfather, I have a daughter.

136
00:11:43,411 --> 00:11:46,979
You see, she and Enzo...

137
00:11:47,023 --> 00:11:50,679
You want Enzo to stay in this country,
and your daughter to be married.

138
00:11:52,681 --> 00:11:54,900
NAZORINE: You understand
everything.

139
00:11:55,771 --> 00:11:58,121
Mr. Hagen. Thank you.

140
00:12:01,298 --> 00:12:03,518
Wait till you see the beautiful
wedding cake I made for your daughter!

141
00:12:03,561 --> 00:12:05,346
Oof, like this! [CHUCKLES]

142
00:12:05,389 --> 00:12:08,087
The bride and the groom
with the angel...

143
00:12:13,266 --> 00:12:14,355
Who should I give
this job to?

144
00:12:15,094 --> 00:12:18,010
Not to our paisan.

145
00:12:18,054 --> 00:12:23,102
Give it to a Jew Congressman in another
district. Who else is on the list?

146
00:12:30,153 --> 00:12:31,807
Hey, Michael!

147
00:12:31,850 --> 00:12:33,374
[ALL GREETING]

148
00:12:51,566 --> 00:12:55,308
TOM: He's not on the list,
but Luca Brasi wants to see you.

149
00:13:00,836 --> 00:13:03,360
Is this...
Is this necessary?

150
00:13:03,404 --> 00:13:06,581
He didn't expect to be invited to the
wedding, so he wanted to thank you.

151
00:13:06,624 --> 00:13:09,322
All right.

152
00:13:09,366 --> 00:13:14,763
Don Corleone, I'm honored and grateful
that you have invited me to your home

153
00:13:14,806 --> 00:13:17,635
on the wedding day
of your daughter.

154
00:13:17,679 --> 00:13:20,116
May their first child
be a masculine child.

155
00:13:21,291 --> 00:13:22,684
Michael...

156
00:13:24,555 --> 00:13:27,950
That man over there
is talking to himself.

157
00:13:27,993 --> 00:13:30,866
See that scary guy
over there?

158
00:13:30,909 --> 00:13:32,607
He's a very scary guy.

159
00:13:32,650 --> 00:13:34,478
Well, who is he?
What's his name?

160
00:13:34,522 --> 00:13:39,135
His name is Luca Brasi.
He helps my father out sometimes.

161
00:13:40,919 --> 00:13:43,182
Oh Michael, wait...
He's coming over here!

162
00:13:43,226 --> 00:13:45,446
Michael!
[EXCLAIMS]

163
00:13:45,489 --> 00:13:46,969
Hey!

164
00:13:48,144 --> 00:13:50,015
You look terrific!

165
00:13:50,059 --> 00:13:52,322
My brother Tom Hagen,
Miss Kay Adams.

166
00:13:52,365 --> 00:13:53,845
How do you do?
Nice to meet you. How do you do, Tom?

167
00:13:55,107 --> 00:13:57,632
Your father's been
asking for you.

168
00:13:57,675 --> 00:13:58,720
Very nice to meet you.

169
00:13:58,763 --> 00:14:00,243
Nice to meet you.

170
00:14:02,114 --> 00:14:04,813
If he's your brother,
why does he have a different name?

171
00:14:04,856 --> 00:14:07,163
Oh, back when my brother,
Sonny, was a kid,

172
00:14:07,206 --> 00:14:08,817
he found Tom Hagen
on the street.

173
00:14:08,860 --> 00:14:12,734
And he had no home, and so
my father took him in.

174
00:14:14,518 --> 00:14:15,911
And he's been with us
ever since.

175
00:14:17,695 --> 00:14:19,610
He's a good lawyer.

176
00:14:20,481 --> 00:14:22,831
Not a Sicilian.

177
00:14:22,874 --> 00:14:25,094
I think he's going
to be consigliere.

178
00:14:25,137 --> 00:14:26,225
What's that?

179
00:14:26,269 --> 00:14:28,140
That's a,

180
00:14:28,184 --> 00:14:31,927
like a counselor, an advisor.
Very important to the family.

181
00:14:32,971 --> 00:14:35,017
You like your lasagna?

182
00:14:39,369 --> 00:14:41,632
Don Corleone.

183
00:14:41,676 --> 00:14:44,417
I am honored and grateful

184
00:14:44,461 --> 00:14:48,509
that you have invited me
to your daughter's wedding.

185
00:14:48,552 --> 00:14:50,162
[PAPER RUSTLING]

186
00:14:53,296 --> 00:14:56,647
On the day of
your daughter's wedding.

187
00:14:56,691 --> 00:15:01,522
And I hope that their first
child will be a masculine child.

188
00:15:02,914 --> 00:15:08,006
I pledge my
ever-ending loyalty.

189
00:15:10,052 --> 00:15:12,054
For your daughter's
bridal purse.

190
00:15:12,097 --> 00:15:15,405
Thank you, Luca.
My most valued friend.

191
00:15:15,448 --> 00:15:20,541
Don Corleone, I'm going to leave
you now, because I know you're busy.

192
00:15:21,150 --> 00:15:22,543
Thank you.

193
00:16:05,063 --> 00:16:06,021
[ALL SINGING]

194
00:16:12,244 --> 00:16:14,551
SignoraCorleone!

195
00:16:15,552 --> 00:16:18,686
No! No! No!

196
00:16:18,729 --> 00:16:20,644
[CHATTERING]

197
00:16:23,516 --> 00:16:25,170
[SPEAKING ITALIAN]

198
00:16:27,608 --> 00:16:29,392
[SINGING CHE LA LUNA]

199
00:17:23,707 --> 00:17:25,187
[ALL SINGING]

200
00:17:27,450 --> 00:17:32,673
Senator Cauley apologized for not coming
personally, but said you'd understand.

201
00:17:32,716 --> 00:17:36,894
Also some of the judges.
They've all sent gifts.

202
00:17:36,938 --> 00:17:38,374
[TOASTING IN ITALIAN]

203
00:17:38,417 --> 00:17:40,071
[WOMEN SCREAMING]

204
00:17:40,115 --> 00:17:41,290
What is that outside?

205
00:17:50,386 --> 00:17:54,869
Johnny! Johnny! Johnny!

206
00:17:56,000 --> 00:17:57,654
I love you!

207
00:18:00,657 --> 00:18:02,441
[SCREAMING CONTINUES]

208
00:18:07,882 --> 00:18:10,145
He came all the way from
California to come to the wedding.

209
00:18:10,188 --> 00:18:11,494
I told you he was
going to come!

210
00:18:11,537 --> 00:18:13,365
Been two years.
He's probably in trouble again.

211
00:18:13,409 --> 00:18:14,932
He's a good godson.

212
00:18:15,933 --> 00:18:20,285
Johnny, Johnny!
Sing a song!

213
00:18:20,329 --> 00:18:21,809
[ALL CHEERING]

214
00:18:36,301 --> 00:18:38,826
You never said
you knew Johnny Fontane!

215
00:18:38,869 --> 00:18:40,436
Sure.
You want to meet him?

216
00:18:40,479 --> 00:18:42,917
Huh? Oh...
Great! Sure.

217
00:18:42,960 --> 00:18:45,310
My father helped him
with his career.

218
00:18:45,354 --> 00:18:46,834
He did?

219
00:18:46,877 --> 00:18:48,052
How?

220
00:18:48,096 --> 00:18:50,098
[JOHNNY SINGING
I HAVE BUT ONE HEART]

221
00:18:50,141 --> 00:18:52,622
Let's listen to this song.
No, Michael...

222
00:18:52,665 --> 00:18:57,540
[WOMEN SCREAMING]
♪ This heart I bring you

223
00:18:58,715 --> 00:19:03,111
♪ I have but one heart

224
00:19:03,154 --> 00:19:05,853
♪ To share with you

225
00:19:07,942 --> 00:19:11,859
♪ I have but one dream

226
00:19:12,729 --> 00:19:16,777
♪ That I can cling to

227
00:19:17,647 --> 00:19:22,260
♪ You are the one dream

228
00:19:22,304 --> 00:19:25,437
♪ I pray comes true

229
00:19:26,656 --> 00:19:28,919
Please, Michael. Tell me.

230
00:19:28,963 --> 00:19:32,488
♪ My, darling,
until I saw you ♪

231
00:19:32,531 --> 00:19:33,968
Well, when Johnny
was first starting out,

232
00:19:34,011 --> 00:19:37,406
he was signed to this
personal service contract

233
00:19:37,449 --> 00:19:40,409
with a big bandleader.

234
00:19:40,452 --> 00:19:42,541
And as his career
got better and better,

235
00:19:42,585 --> 00:19:45,675
he wanted to get out of it.

236
00:19:45,718 --> 00:19:48,504
Now, Johnny
is my father's godson.

237
00:19:48,547 --> 00:19:51,855
And my father went
to see this bandleader.

238
00:19:51,899 --> 00:19:55,598
And he offered him $10,000
to let Johnny go,

239
00:19:55,641 --> 00:19:58,557
but the bandleader
said no.

240
00:19:58,601 --> 00:20:00,821
So the next day

241
00:20:00,864 --> 00:20:04,302
my father went to see him,
only this time with Luca Brasi.

242
00:20:06,000 --> 00:20:08,437
And within an hour,

243
00:20:08,480 --> 00:20:13,921
he signed a release for a
certified check of $1,000.

244
00:20:15,618 --> 00:20:17,402
Well, how did he do that?

245
00:20:17,446 --> 00:20:19,404
My father made him an
offer he couldn't refuse.

246
00:20:21,015 --> 00:20:21,972
What was that?

247
00:20:23,408 --> 00:20:26,281
Luca Brasi held a gun
to his head,

248
00:20:26,324 --> 00:20:28,500
and my father assured him
that either his brain

249
00:20:28,544 --> 00:20:31,503
or his signature
would be on the contract.

250
00:20:36,552 --> 00:20:38,032
That's a true story.

251
00:20:39,642 --> 00:20:41,426
[SINGING IN ITALIAN]

252
00:20:49,652 --> 00:20:52,263
That's my family, Kay.
