Go on.

495
00:39:04,920 --> 00:39:07,749
Tom, what...
What is this nonsense?

496
00:39:07,792 --> 00:39:11,100
It's from Johnny.
He's starring in that new film.

497
00:39:11,144 --> 00:39:12,406
Huh.

498
00:39:13,537 --> 00:39:14,712
Take it away.

499
00:39:14,756 --> 00:39:16,062
Take it over there.

500
00:39:17,367 --> 00:39:18,847
And, uh...

501
00:39:19,848 --> 00:39:22,111
tell Luca Brasi
to come in.

502
00:39:28,204 --> 00:39:31,642
I'm a little worried
about this Sollozzo fellow.

503
00:39:31,686 --> 00:39:34,297
I want you to find out what he's
got under his fingernails, you know.

504
00:39:35,646 --> 00:39:39,476
Go to the Tattaglias.

505
00:39:39,520 --> 00:39:43,741
Make them think that you're
not too happy with our family

506
00:39:45,134 --> 00:39:47,484
and find out
what you can.

507
00:39:53,621 --> 00:39:57,233
[HAVE YOURSELF A MERRY LITTLE
CHRISTMAS PLAYING ON RADIO]

508
00:39:59,453 --> 00:40:03,065
♪ Let your heart be light

509
00:40:05,024 --> 00:40:08,375
I got something for your
mother and for Sonny

510
00:40:08,418 --> 00:40:13,075
and a tie for Freddy,
and Tom Hagen got the Reynolds pen.

511
00:40:13,119 --> 00:40:14,337
What do you want
for Christmas?

512
00:40:14,381 --> 00:40:16,339
Me? Oh... Just you.

513
00:40:20,126 --> 00:40:23,520
[ON RADIO]
♪ Make the Yule-tide gay

514
00:40:25,044 --> 00:40:31,093
♪ From now on our troubles
will be miles away

515
00:40:35,097 --> 00:40:39,884
♪ Here we are
as in olden days

516
00:40:39,928 --> 00:40:43,801
♪ Happy golden days of yore

517
00:40:45,499 --> 00:40:46,804
♪ Faithful friends... ♪

518
00:40:48,067 --> 00:40:50,112
VITO: Andiamo, Fredo.

519
00:40:50,156 --> 00:40:51,766
Tell Paulie to get the car.
We're going.

520
00:40:51,809 --> 00:40:53,594
FREDO: Okay, Pop.

521
00:40:53,637 --> 00:40:55,248
I'll have to get it
myself, Pa.

522
00:40:55,291 --> 00:40:57,511
Paulie called in
sick this morning.

523
00:40:59,382 --> 00:41:02,603
Paulie's a good kid.
I don't mind getting the car.

524
00:41:05,997 --> 00:41:08,043
Buon natale, Caro.
Grazie.

525
00:41:50,868 --> 00:41:54,394
Luca!
I'm Bruno Tattaglia.

526
00:41:54,437 --> 00:41:56,135
I know.

527
00:41:56,178 --> 00:42:00,182
[BOTH SPEAKING ITALIAN]

528
00:42:04,926 --> 00:42:06,406
You know who I am?

529
00:42:06,449 --> 00:42:08,756
I know you.

530
00:42:08,799 --> 00:42:11,715
You have been talking to the
Tattaglia family... right?

531
00:42:13,152 --> 00:42:17,591
I think you and I
can do business.

532
00:42:19,549 --> 00:42:21,682
I need someone strong like you.

533
00:42:22,552 --> 00:42:25,990
I heard you are not happy...

534
00:42:26,034 --> 00:42:28,210
...with the Corleone family.

535
00:42:29,037 --> 00:42:32,083
Want to join me?

536
00:42:32,127 --> 00:42:33,781
What's in it for me?

537
00:42:34,738 --> 00:42:36,653
$50,000 to start with.

538
00:42:41,484 --> 00:42:42,616
Not bad.

539
00:42:44,052 --> 00:42:45,923
Agreed?

540
00:43:03,550 --> 00:43:05,204
[SPEAKING ITALIAN]

541
00:43:09,599 --> 00:43:10,905
[GRUNTING]

542
00:43:16,911 --> 00:43:18,217
[CHOKING]

543
00:43:20,741 --> 00:43:22,046
[GASPING]

544
00:43:45,200 --> 00:43:49,030
Tom! Tom Hagen.
Merry Christmas.

545
00:43:49,073 --> 00:43:52,120
Hey! I'm glad I ran into you.
I want to talk to you.

546
00:43:52,163 --> 00:43:54,209
Well, I haven't got time.

547
00:43:54,253 --> 00:43:59,083
Make time, Consigliere.
Get in the car.

548
00:43:59,127 --> 00:44:03,610
What are you worried about? If I wanted
to kill you, you'd be dead already.

549
00:44:03,653 --> 00:44:05,351
Get in.

550
00:44:05,394 --> 00:44:07,353
[CAROLS PLAYING ON RADIO]

551
00:44:16,231 --> 00:44:18,625
Fredo, I'm going to
buy some fruit.

552
00:44:18,668 --> 00:44:19,843
Okay, Pop.

553
00:44:26,720 --> 00:44:29,505
Merry Christmas.
I want some fruit.

554
00:45:30,174 --> 00:45:32,046
[WHIMPERING]

555
00:45:40,533 --> 00:45:42,230
[SOBBING]

556
00:45:49,063 --> 00:45:50,456
[SHOUTING]

557
00:45:52,893 --> 00:45:54,373
[BELL TOLLING]

558
00:45:57,201 --> 00:45:59,421
Mike, Would you like me
better if I were a nun?

559
00:45:59,465 --> 00:46:01,162
Like in the story.

560
00:46:04,078 --> 00:46:05,775
No.

561
00:46:05,819 --> 00:46:08,125
Well then, would you like me
better if I were Ingrid Bergman?

562
00:46:08,169 --> 00:46:09,518
Now, that's a thought.

563
00:46:12,042 --> 00:46:14,175
Michael.

564
00:46:14,218 --> 00:46:17,134
No, I wouldn't like you better
if you were Ingrid Bergman.

565
00:46:17,178 --> 00:46:18,875
Mike.
What's the matter?

566
00:46:35,414 --> 00:46:38,025
They don't say
if he's dead or alive.

567
00:46:45,336 --> 00:46:46,816
[HORN BLARING]

568
00:47:00,351 --> 00:47:01,875
Sonny, Michael.

569
00:47:01,918 --> 00:47:03,572
Michael, where you been?

570
00:47:03,616 --> 00:47:05,182
Is he all right?

571
00:47:05,226 --> 00:47:06,532
We don't know yet.

572
00:47:06,575 --> 00:47:09,360
There are all
kinds of stories.

573
00:47:09,404 --> 00:47:10,623
He was hit bad, Mikey.

574
00:47:12,451 --> 00:47:13,800
Are you there?

575
00:47:13,843 --> 00:47:15,976
Yeah, I'm here.

576
00:47:16,019 --> 00:47:18,152
Where have you been?
I was worried.

577
00:47:18,195 --> 00:47:20,502
Didn't Tom tell you
I called?

578
00:47:20,546 --> 00:47:22,809
No. Look, come home, kid.

579
00:47:22,852 --> 00:47:24,985
You should be with Mama,
you hear? All right.

580
00:47:32,514 --> 00:47:33,994
SANDRA: Oh, my God.

581
00:47:35,865 --> 00:47:36,866
[CLATTERING]

582
00:47:36,910 --> 00:47:37,954
[GASPING]

583
00:47:37,998 --> 00:47:39,565
Sonny!

584
00:47:39,608 --> 00:47:41,044
[BABY CRYING]

585
00:47:45,962 --> 00:47:47,877
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

586
00:47:48,399 --> 00:47:50,750
Stay back there.

587
00:47:50,793 --> 00:47:53,448
Who is it?
Open up, it's Clemenza.

588
00:47:55,929 --> 00:47:59,193
There's more news
about your old man.

589
00:47:59,236 --> 00:48:01,151
Word is out that
he's already dead.

590
00:48:01,195 --> 00:48:03,327
What's the matter...
What's the matter with you?

591
00:48:03,371 --> 00:48:05,634
Take it easy!
Take it easy!

592
00:48:05,678 --> 00:48:07,027
Where was Paulie?

593
00:48:07,070 --> 00:48:09,029
Paulie was out sick.
He's been sick all winter.

594
00:48:09,072 --> 00:48:10,204
How many times
he been sick?

595
00:48:10,247 --> 00:48:12,032
Only maybe three, four times.

596
00:48:12,075 --> 00:48:13,816
I mean, I asked Freddy if he wants
me to get a different bodyguard

597
00:48:13,860 --> 00:48:15,818
He said no. Pick him up now.
Do me a favour, pick him up right now.

598
00:48:15,862 --> 00:48:17,733
I don't care how sick he is.
If he's breathing,

599
00:48:17,777 --> 00:48:20,301
I want you to bring him to my father's
house now, you understand? Now.

600
00:48:20,344 --> 00:48:21,781
Yeah, You want me to
send any people over here?

601
00:48:21,824 --> 00:48:23,913
No, no, no. Just you and him.
Go ahead.

602
00:48:23,957 --> 00:48:25,393
[BABY CRYING]

603
00:48:30,659 --> 00:48:32,748
Okay, I'm...

604
00:48:32,792 --> 00:48:35,098
I'm going to have a couple of our people
come over to the house. Couple of our people.

605
00:48:35,142 --> 00:48:36,883
[TELEPHONE RINGING]

606
00:48:39,538 --> 00:48:40,626
Hello?

607
00:48:40,669 --> 00:48:41,801
SOLLOZZO:
Santino Corleone?

608
00:48:41,844 --> 00:48:44,717
Yeah.
We have Tom Hagen.

609
00:48:44,760 --> 00:48:48,547
You got three hours he'll be
released with our proposition.

610
00:48:48,590 --> 00:48:51,985
Listen to everything he has
to say before you do anything.

611
00:48:52,028 --> 00:48:53,508
What's done is done.

612
00:48:53,552 --> 00:48:56,642
And don't lose that famous
temper of yours, eh, Sonny?

613
00:48:56,685 --> 00:48:58,382
I'll wait.

614
00:48:58,426 --> 00:49:00,036
[HANGS UP]

615
00:49:12,571 --> 00:49:14,573
SOLLOZZO:
Your boss is dead.

616
00:49:17,619 --> 00:49:19,926
I know you're not in the
muscle end of the family, Tom,

617
00:49:19,969 --> 00:49:23,059
so I don't want
you to be scared.

618
00:49:23,103 --> 00:49:26,410
I want you to help the Corleones
and I want you to help me.

619
00:49:30,937 --> 00:49:35,419
Yeah, we got him outside his office just
about an hour after we picked you up.

620
00:49:36,899 --> 00:49:38,074
Drink it.

621
00:49:42,818 --> 00:49:46,039
So now, It's up to you to make
the peace between me and Sonny.

622
00:49:50,609 --> 00:49:53,307
Sonny was hot for my deal,
wasn't he?

623
00:49:54,787 --> 00:49:56,440
And you knew it was
the right thing to do.

624
00:49:58,791 --> 00:50:01,881
Sonny will come after you
with everything he's got.

625
00:50:01,924 --> 00:50:03,796
That will be his
first reaction, sure.

626
00:50:05,145 --> 00:50:08,148
So you gotta talk
some sense into him.

627
00:50:08,191 --> 00:50:11,934
The Tattaglia family is behind
me with all their people.

628
00:50:11,978 --> 00:50:17,070
The other New York families will go along with
anything that will prevent the full-scale war.

629
00:50:17,113 --> 00:50:19,638
Let's face it, Tom
and all due respect,

630
00:50:19,681 --> 00:50:22,249
the Don, rest in peace,
was slipping.

631
00:50:25,295 --> 00:50:26,993
Ten years ago,
could I have gotten to him?

632
00:50:32,172 --> 00:50:33,521
Well, now he's dead.

633
00:50:33,564 --> 00:50:36,089
He's dead, Tom,
and nothing can bring him back.

634
00:50:37,786 --> 00:50:40,180
So you gotta talk to Sonny,

635
00:50:40,223 --> 00:50:44,445
You gotta talk to the Caporegimes,
Tessio, and that fat Clemenza.

636
00:50:48,667 --> 00:50:49,972
It's good business, Tom.

637
00:50:52,235 --> 00:50:57,414
I'll try. But even Sonny won't
be able to call off Luca Brasi.

638
00:51:00,069 --> 00:51:01,897
Yeah, well...

639
00:51:03,638 --> 00:51:06,162
Let me worry about Luca.

640
00:51:11,385 --> 00:51:13,648
You just talk to Sonny.

641
00:51:13,692 --> 00:51:16,042
And the other two kids.

642
00:51:19,045 --> 00:51:20,350
I'll do my best.

643
00:51:20,960 --> 00:51:22,178
Good.

644
00:51:23,876 --> 00:51:26,705
Now you can go.

645
00:51:33,059 --> 00:51:35,626
I don't like violence, Tom.

646
00:51:35,670 --> 00:51:37,890
I'm a businessman.

647
00:51:37,933 --> 00:51:40,457
Blood is a big expense.

648
00:51:43,460 --> 00:51:45,985
[HORN HONKING]

649
00:52:01,435 --> 00:52:03,393
He's still alive.

650
00:52:03,437 --> 00:52:07,484
They hit him with five
shots, and he's still alive!

651
00:52:07,528 --> 00:52:12,141
That's bad luck for me, and bad luck
for you if you don't make that deal.

652
00:52:56,925 --> 00:52:58,971
Your mother is over in the
hospital with your father.

653
00:52:59,014 --> 00:53:01,843
Looks like he's gonna
pull through. Thank God.

654
00:53:03,714 --> 00:53:06,108
It's a lot of
bad blood.

655
00:53:06,152 --> 00:53:10,373
Sollozzo, Philip Tattaglia,
Bruno Tattaglia, Ramon...

656
00:53:10,417 --> 00:53:11,635
MICHAEL: You gonna
kill all those guys?

657
00:53:11,679 --> 00:53:13,637
Hey, stay out of it, Mickey.
Do me a favour.

658
00:53:13,681 --> 00:53:16,379
TOM: Sollozzo's the key, you get rid
of him, everything falls into line.

659
00:53:16,423 --> 00:53:20,819
What about Luca?
Sollozzo thinks he can control him.

660
00:53:20,862 --> 00:53:24,648
I don't know if Luca sold out, we're in a
lot of trouble. Believe me, lot of trouble.

661
00:53:24,692 --> 00:53:26,302
Has anyone been
in touch with Luca?

662
00:53:26,346 --> 00:53:28,391
Yeah, we've been trying all night.
He might be shacked up.

663
00:53:28,435 --> 00:53:29,740
Hey, Mickey, do me a favor...

664
00:53:29,784 --> 00:53:32,395
TOM: Luca never
sleeps over with a broad.

665
00:53:34,484 --> 00:53:37,923
Well, Tom,
you're consigliere.

666
00:53:37,966 --> 00:53:40,839
What do we do if the old man dies?
God forbid.

667
00:53:40,882 --> 00:53:44,103
If we lose the old man,

668
00:53:44,146 --> 00:53:47,193
we lose the political contacts
and half our strength.

669
00:53:47,236 --> 00:53:50,109
The other New York families
might wind up supporting Sollozzo

670
00:53:50,152 --> 00:53:52,894
just to avoid a long,
destructive war.

671
00:53:52,938 --> 00:53:57,507
This is almost 1946.
Nobody wants bloodshed anymore.

672
00:53:57,551 --> 00:53:59,031
If your father dies,

673
00:54:01,642 --> 00:54:03,513
you make the deal, Sonny.

674
00:54:03,557 --> 00:54:06,125
You know, that's easy for you to
say, Tom. He's not your father.

675
00:54:06,168 --> 00:54:07,909
I was as much a son
to him, as you or Mike.

676
00:54:11,652 --> 00:54:12,914
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

677
00:54:12,958 --> 00:54:14,481
What is it?

678
00:54:15,482 --> 00:54:17,963
Paulie, I told you
to stay put.

679
00:54:18,006 --> 00:54:19,442
Well, the guy
at the gates. They...

680
00:54:19,486 --> 00:54:21,314
They said they
got a package. Yeah?

681
00:54:21,357 --> 00:54:23,446
Tessio, go see
what it is.

682
00:54:26,667 --> 00:54:27,798
You want me
to hang around?

683
00:54:27,842 --> 00:54:29,104
SONNY: Yeah, hang around.
You all right?

684
00:54:29,148 --> 00:54:30,758
Yeah, I'm fine.
Yeah?

685
00:54:30,801 --> 00:54:33,195
There's some food in the house.
Are you hungry or anything?

686
00:54:33,239 --> 00:54:35,197
No, it's all right.

687
00:54:35,241 --> 00:54:36,590
How about a drink? How about a little
brandy? It's good to sweat it out.

688
00:54:36,633 --> 00:54:38,244
All right, sure.
Go ahead.

689
00:54:38,287 --> 00:54:41,116
That might be
a good idea. Yeah, right.

690
00:54:41,160 --> 00:54:43,292
I want you to take care of that
son-of-a-bitch, right away.

691
00:54:43,336 --> 00:54:45,773
Paulie sold out
the old man. That stronz...

692
00:54:45,816 --> 00:54:47,340
I don't wanna
see him again.

693
00:54:47,383 --> 00:54:49,255
Make that the first thing on your list.
Understand?

694
00:54:49,298 --> 00:54:50,517
Understood.

695
00:54:50,560 --> 00:54:52,040
Hey, Mickey, tomorrow,

696
00:54:52,084 --> 00:54:53,824
You get a couple of guys,
you go over to Luca's apartment.

697
00:54:53,868 --> 00:54:55,652
Hang around,
wait for him to show up.

698
00:54:55,696 --> 00:54:58,960
Uh, maybe we shouldn't get Mike
mixed up in this too directly.

699
00:55:01,397 --> 00:55:04,879
Listen, uh... Hanging around the house
on the phone would be a big help, huh.

700
00:55:06,011 --> 00:55:07,882
Try Luca again.

701
00:55:16,804 --> 00:55:17,936
What's the hell is this?

702
00:55:17,979 --> 00:55:19,720
TESSIO: That's
a Sicilian message.

703
00:55:19,763 --> 00:55:22,201
It means Luca Brasi
sleeps with the fishes.

704
00:55:30,383 --> 00:55:32,124
[CHILDREN YELLING]

705
00:55:36,389 --> 00:55:38,521
I'm going now. What time are
you gonna be home tonight?

706
00:55:38,565 --> 00:55:40,175
I don't know.
Probably late.

707
00:55:42,786 --> 00:55:44,658
WOMAN: Don't
forget the cannoli!

708
00:55:44,701 --> 00:55:46,442
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

709
00:55:48,618 --> 00:55:51,230
Rocco, sit on the other side.

710
00:55:51,273 --> 00:55:53,188
You block the
rear-view mirror.

711
00:55:54,624 --> 00:55:56,278
That Sonny's running wild.

712
00:55:56,322 --> 00:55:58,150
He thinking of going
to the mattresses already.

713
00:55:58,193 --> 00:56:01,022
We gotta find a spot
on the West Side.

714
00:56:01,066 --> 00:56:04,025
Try 309 West 43rd Street.

715
00:56:04,069 --> 00:56:06,549
You know any good spots
on the West Side?

716
00:56:06,593 --> 00:56:07,898
Yeah, I'll think about it.

717
00:56:07,942 --> 00:56:09,596
Well, think about it while
you're driving, will ya?

718
00:56:09,639 --> 00:56:11,598
I want to hit New York
sometime this month.

719
00:56:11,641 --> 00:56:13,252
And watch out for the kids
when you're backing out.

720
00:56:24,132 --> 00:56:27,135
CLEMENZA: Hey, Paulie, I want you to
go down 39th Street, Carlo Santos,

721
00:56:27,179 --> 00:56:30,138
pick up 18 mattresses for the guys
to sleep with, you bring me the bill.

722
00:56:30,182 --> 00:56:31,661
PAULIE: Yeah, all right.

723
00:56:31,705 --> 00:56:33,533
CLEMENZA: Make sure
they're clean,

724
00:56:33,576 --> 00:56:36,188
because those guys are gonna be stuck up in there for a long time, you know.

725
00:56:36,231 --> 00:56:38,538
PAULIE: They're clean and they told
me, they exterminate them.

726
00:56:38,581 --> 00:56:40,627
CLEMENZA: [CHUCKLING] That's a bad word to use.

727
00:56:40,670 --> 00:56:44,587
Exterminate! Look at this guy. Watch out, so we don't exterminate you!

728
00:56:44,631 --> 00:56:47,199
[CLEMENZA CHATTERING IN ITALIAN]

729
00:56:47,242 --> 00:56:48,765
[BOTH LAUGHING]

730
00:56:51,246 --> 00:56:53,770
CLEMENZA: Pull over.
I've got to take a leak.

731
00:56:58,601 --> 00:57:00,255
[SHIP HORN BLOWING]

732
00:57:04,607 --> 00:57:06,218
[SEAGULLS CAWING]

733
00:57:20,058 --> 00:57:21,363
[GUNSHOTS]

734
00:57:31,417 --> 00:57:33,071
[CAR DOOR OPENING]

735
00:57:35,464 --> 00:57:38,902
Leave the gun.
Take the cannoli.

736
00:57:57,095 --> 00:58:00,010
CLEMENZA: Hey, Mike!
Hey, Mikey!

737
00:58:01,708 --> 00:58:03,536
Yeah. You're wanted
on the telephone.

738
00:58:10,020 --> 00:58:12,240
Who is it?
Some girl.

739
00:58:16,288 --> 00:58:17,680
Hello. Kay?

740
00:58:17,724 --> 00:58:19,029
KAY: How's your father?

741
00:58:19,073 --> 00:58:20,683
He's good.
He's going to make it.

742
00:58:21,554 --> 00:58:23,338
I love you.

743
00:58:23,686 --> 00:58:24,731
Huh?

744
00:58:24,774 --> 00:58:26,341
I love you!

745
00:58:27,255 --> 00:58:28,517
Michael?

746
00:58:28,561 --> 00:58:29,910
Yeah, I know.

747
00:58:29,953 --> 00:58:31,390
Tell me you love me.

748
00:58:31,433 --> 00:58:32,913
I can't talk.

749
00:58:32,956 --> 00:58:34,871
Can't you say it?

750
00:58:35,785 --> 00:58:38,484
Yeah, I'll see
you tonight.

751
00:58:38,527 --> 00:58:42,009
Hey Mikey, why don't you tell
that nice girl you love her?

752
00:58:42,052 --> 00:58:46,231
I love you with all my heart. If I don't
see you again soon, I'm going to die!

753
00:58:46,274 --> 00:58:47,536
[CLEMENZA CHUCKLING]

754
00:58:47,580 --> 00:58:49,364
Come over here kid,
learn something.

755
00:58:49,408 --> 00:58:52,498
You never know, you might have
to cook for 20 guys some day.

756
00:58:52,541 --> 00:58:56,284
You see, you start out with a little
bit of oil, then you fry some garlic.

757
00:58:56,328 --> 00:59:01,985
Then you throw in some tomatoes, tomato paste,
you fry it and make sure it doesn't stick.

758
00:59:02,029 --> 00:59:06,076
You get it to a boil, you shove in
all your sausage and your meatballs.

759
00:59:07,948 --> 00:59:09,993
Add a little bit
of wine.

760
00:59:13,258 --> 00:59:16,435
And a little bit of sugar.

761
00:59:16,478 --> 00:59:17,784
And that's my trick.

762
00:59:17,827 --> 00:59:19,307
Why don't you cut the crap.

763
00:59:19,351 --> 00:59:22,092
I have more important things
for you to do. How's Paulie?

764
00:59:22,136 --> 00:59:23,703
Oh, Paulie.
Won't see him no more.

765
00:59:25,792 --> 00:59:27,097
Where are you going?

766
00:59:27,141 --> 00:59:28,360
To the city.

767
00:59:28,403 --> 00:59:29,752
Send some bodyguards
with him, all right?

768
00:59:29,796 --> 00:59:30,971
No, I'm just going
to the hospital...

769
00:59:31,014 --> 00:59:32,625
Nevermind, send
somebody with him.

770
00:59:32,668 --> 00:59:35,410
CLEMENZA: He'll be all right.
Sollozzo knows he's a civilian.

771
00:59:35,454 --> 00:59:37,412
Be careful, huh?
Yes, sir.

772
00:59:40,589 --> 00:59:42,330
Send somebody
with him anyway.

773
00:59:53,515 --> 00:59:55,430
[ALL OF MY LIFE
PLAYING ON RADIO]

774
01:00:10,880 --> 01:00:12,926
I have to go.

775
01:00:12,969 --> 01:00:15,755
Can I go with you?

776
01:00:15,798 --> 01:00:20,150
No, Kay. There's gonna be detectives
there, people from the press.

777
01:00:20,194 --> 01:00:22,283
Well, I'll wait
in the cab.

778
01:00:24,938 --> 01:00:27,506
I don't want you
to get involved.

779
01:00:30,291 --> 01:00:31,901
When will
I see you again?

780
01:00:38,865 --> 01:00:41,128
Go back to New Hampshire,

781
01:00:41,171 --> 01:00:42,999
and I'll call you
at your parents' house.

782
01:00:44,827 --> 01:00:46,742
When will I see you
again, Michael?

783
01:00:48,657 --> 01:00:50,224
I don't know.

784
01:01:05,195 --> 01:01:06,501
[DOOR CLOSES]

785
01:03:01,747 --> 01:03:03,313
What are you doing here?

786
01:03:03,357 --> 01:03:05,620
You're not supposed
to be here now.

787
01:03:05,664 --> 01:03:09,232
I'm Michael Corleone.
This is my father.

788
01:03:09,276 --> 01:03:11,626
There's nobody here.
What happened to the guards?

789
01:03:11,670 --> 01:03:14,107
Your father just had
too many visitors.

790
01:03:14,150 --> 01:03:17,153
They interfered
with hospital service.

791
01:03:17,197 --> 01:03:20,461
The police made them leave
about 10 minutes ago.

792
01:03:25,031 --> 01:03:28,948
Get me Long Beach
45620, please.

793
01:03:31,516 --> 01:03:33,822
Nurse. Wait a minute.
Stay here.

794
01:03:37,957 --> 01:03:40,089
Sonny, Michael.
I'm at the hospital.

795
01:03:40,133 --> 01:03:42,918
Listen, I got here late,
there's nobody here. SONNY: What? Nobody?

796
01:03:42,962 --> 01:03:47,183
Nobody. No Tessio's men, no
detectives, nobody. Papa's all alone.

797
01:03:47,227 --> 01:03:48,663
Don't panic.

798
01:03:48,707 --> 01:03:49,838
I won't panic.

799
01:03:51,231 --> 01:03:54,321
I'm sorry,
but you will have to leave.

800
01:03:54,364 --> 01:03:56,845
Uh...

801
01:03:56,889 --> 01:03:59,718
You and I are going to move
my father to another room.

802
01:03:59,761 --> 01:04:02,764
Now, can you disconnect those
tubes so we can move the bed out?

803
01:04:02,808 --> 01:04:04,113
That's out of
the question!

804
01:04:04,157 --> 01:04:06,376
Do you know my father?

805
01:04:06,420 --> 01:04:08,466
Men are coming
here to kill him.

806
01:04:08,509 --> 01:04:10,859
Do you understand?

807
01:04:10,903 --> 01:04:12,600
Now, help me, please.

808
01:04:39,148 --> 01:04:40,628
[DOOR CLOSING]

809
01:04:41,586 --> 01:04:43,457
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

810
01:05:29,764 --> 01:05:30,809
Who are you?

811
01:05:30,852 --> 01:05:33,551
I am Enzo, the baker.

812
01:05:34,595 --> 01:05:35,814
Do you remember me?
Enzo.

813
01:05:35,857 --> 01:05:37,250
Yes, Enzo.

814
01:05:37,293 --> 01:05:39,948
You'd better go,
there's going to be trouble.

815
01:05:39,992 --> 01:05:42,298
If there is trouble,
I'll stay here to help you.

816
01:05:42,342 --> 01:05:44,605
For your father.
For your father.

817
01:05:45,780 --> 01:05:48,870
All right. Listen.
Wait for me outside,

818
01:05:48,914 --> 01:05:50,655
in front of the hospital,
all right?

819
01:05:50,698 --> 01:05:52,657
I'll be out in a minute.
Go ahead.Okay.

820
01:06:06,758 --> 01:06:10,457
Just lie here, Pop.
I'll take care of you now.

821
01:06:12,198 --> 01:06:14,461
I'm with you now.

822
01:06:15,897 --> 01:06:17,377
I'm with you.

823
01:06:52,891 --> 01:06:55,981
Get rid of these.
Come here.

824
01:06:56,024 --> 01:07:00,420
Put your hand in your pocket, like
you have a gun. You'll be all right.

825
01:07:02,770 --> 01:07:04,250
[MICHAEL SIGHS]

826
01:07:05,991 --> 01:07:07,035
[WHISPERING]
You'll be okay.

827
01:07:18,699 --> 01:07:20,309
[CAR APPROACHING]

828
01:07:51,819 --> 01:07:53,473
You did good.

829
01:08:09,271 --> 01:08:10,882
[SIRENS WAILING]

830
01:08:24,939 --> 01:08:28,943
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

831
01:08:42,087 --> 01:08:44,002
I thought I got all you
Guinea hoods locked up!

832
01:08:44,045 --> 01:08:45,438
What the hell
are you doing here?

833
01:08:45,481 --> 01:08:48,136
What happened to the men
who were guarding my father?

834
01:08:48,180 --> 01:08:50,008
Why, you little punk!

835
01:08:50,051 --> 01:08:51,879
What the hell are you doing
telling me my business!

836
01:08:51,923 --> 01:08:54,055
I pulled them
guys offa here, eh.

837
01:08:54,099 --> 01:08:57,145
Now you get outta here and
stay away from this hospital!

838
01:08:57,189 --> 01:09:00,018
I'm not moving until you put some
guys around my father's room.

839
01:09:00,627 --> 01:09:02,672
Phil, take him in!

840
01:09:02,716 --> 01:09:04,283
The kid's clean, Captain.

841
01:09:04,326 --> 01:09:05,632
He's a war hero.
He's never been...

842
01:09:05,675 --> 01:09:08,113
God damn it.
I said take him in!

843
01:09:10,289 --> 01:09:12,639
What's The Turk paying you
to set up my father, Captain?

844
01:09:13,945 --> 01:09:16,556
Take a hold of him.
Stand him up.

845
01:09:16,599 --> 01:09:18,079
Stand him up straight.

846
01:09:19,385 --> 01:09:20,386
[GRUNTS]

847
01:09:22,692 --> 01:09:24,999
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

848
01:09:40,362 --> 01:09:42,669
I'm the attorney for
the Corleone family.

849
01:09:42,712 --> 01:09:46,151
These men are private detectives
hired to protect Vito Corleone.

850
01:09:46,194 --> 01:09:48,675
They're licensed
to carry firearms.

851
01:09:48,718 --> 01:09:50,633
If you interfere, you'll have
to appear before the judge

852
01:09:50,677 --> 01:09:52,331
in the morning
and show cause.

853
01:09:53,201 --> 01:09:54,550
All right.
Let him go.

854
01:09:55,987 --> 01:09:57,162
Come on.

855
01:10:27,583 --> 01:10:29,585
What's with
all the new faces?

856
01:10:29,629 --> 01:10:31,544
We'll need
them now.

857
01:10:31,587 --> 01:10:34,547
After the hospital thing,
Sonny got mad.

858
01:10:34,590 --> 01:10:37,463
We hit Bruno Tattaglia
four o'clock this morning.

859
01:10:38,856 --> 01:10:40,379
Jesus Christ.

860
01:10:47,560 --> 01:10:49,475
Looks like
a fortress around here.

861
01:10:52,173 --> 01:10:54,567
Tamaduch! Hey...

862
01:10:54,610 --> 01:10:57,657
A 100 buttonmen on the
street 24 hours a day.

863
01:10:57,700 --> 01:11:00,660
That Turk shows one hair
on his ass, he's dead.

864
01:11:03,271 --> 01:11:05,317
Hey, Mike, come here.
Let me look at you.

865
01:11:09,408 --> 01:11:12,585
You're beautiful, beautiful.
You're gorgeous.

866
01:11:12,628 --> 01:11:13,847
Hey, listen to this.

867
01:11:13,891 --> 01:11:15,675
The Turk, he wants to talk!

868
01:11:15,718 --> 01:11:18,243
Imagine the nerve
of the son-of-a-bitch, eh?

869
01:11:18,286 --> 01:11:20,158
Craps all last night.
He wants a meeting today.

870
01:11:20,201 --> 01:11:21,376
What did he say?

871
01:11:21,420 --> 01:11:23,683
What did he say...
[BABBLING]

872
01:11:23,726 --> 01:11:26,033
He wants us to send Michael
to hear the proposition.

873
01:11:26,077 --> 01:11:28,993
And he promises that the deal
is too good to refuse.

874
01:11:29,036 --> 01:11:30,995
Eh?
What about Bruno Tattaglia?

875
01:11:31,038 --> 01:11:32,692
That's part
of the deal.

876
01:11:32,735 --> 01:11:34,868
Bruno cancels out what
they did to my Father.

877
01:11:34,912 --> 01:11:37,088
Sonny, we ought to hear
what they have to say.

878
01:11:37,131 --> 01:11:40,395
No. No. No more!
Not this time, Consigliere.

879
01:11:40,439 --> 01:11:43,964
No more meetings, no more discussions,
no more or Sollozzo tricks.

880
01:11:44,008 --> 01:11:45,835
You give them one message.
I want Sollozzo,

881
01:11:45,879 --> 01:11:47,098
or then it's all out war,
we go to ...

882
01:11:47,141 --> 01:11:48,621
The other families
won't sit still...

883
01:11:48,664 --> 01:11:50,318
They hand me
Sollozzo!

884
01:11:50,362 --> 01:11:52,712
I don't want to hear this!
This is business, not personal!

885
01:11:52,755 --> 01:11:54,583
They shot my father...

886
01:11:54,627 --> 01:11:57,891
Even the issue with your father
was business, not personal, Sonny.

887
01:11:57,935 --> 01:11:59,893
Well, then business will have to
suffer, all right?

888
01:11:59,937 --> 01:12:01,721
And listen,
do me a favor, Tom.

889
01:12:01,764 --> 01:12:03,592
No more advice
on how to patch things up.

890
01:12:03,636 --> 01:12:05,290
Just help me win,
please, all right?

891
01:12:10,730 --> 01:12:12,514
[SIGHS]

892
01:12:12,558 --> 01:12:14,777
I found out about this Captain
McCluskey, who broke Mike's jaw.

893
01:12:14,821 --> 01:12:16,518
What about him?

894
01:12:16,562 --> 01:12:19,173
He's definitely on Sollozzo's
payroll, and for big money.

895
01:12:19,217 --> 01:12:20,609
See?

896
01:12:20,653 --> 01:12:22,481
McCluskey has agreed
to be The Turk's bodyguard.

897
01:12:22,524 --> 01:12:24,526
What you have
to understand, Sonny,

898
01:12:24,570 --> 01:12:28,356
is that while Sollozzo is being
guarded like this, he's invulnerable.

899
01:12:28,400 --> 01:12:32,099
Nobody has ever gunned down a
New York police captain. Never.

900
01:12:32,143 --> 01:12:35,320
It would be disastrous. All the five
families would come after you, Sonny.

901
01:12:35,363 --> 01:12:38,105
The Corleone family
would be outcasts!

902
01:12:38,149 --> 01:12:41,239
Even the old man's political
protection would run for cover.

903
01:12:43,284 --> 01:12:47,114
So, do me a favor.
Take this into consideration.

904
01:12:49,377 --> 01:12:50,770
[SIGHS]

905
01:12:50,813 --> 01:12:52,380
All right, we'll wait.

906
01:12:58,212 --> 01:13:02,521
We can't wait.
We can't wait.

907
01:13:02,564 --> 01:13:04,392
I don't care what Sollozzo
says, about a deal,

908
01:13:04,436 --> 01:13:06,742
he's going to kill Pop.
That's it.

909
01:13:06,786 --> 01:13:09,571
That's the key for him.
We've got to get Sollozzo.

910
01:13:10,442 --> 01:13:12,313
Mike is right.

911
01:13:12,357 --> 01:13:14,881
SONNY: Let me ask you something.
I mean...

912
01:13:14,924 --> 01:13:17,797
What about
this McCluskey, eh?

913
01:13:17,840 --> 01:13:19,712
What do we do
with this cop here?

914
01:13:24,543 --> 01:13:26,545
They want to have a meeting with
me, right?

915
01:13:28,460 --> 01:13:32,855
It will be me,
McCluskey and Sollozzo.

916
01:13:34,727 --> 01:13:36,120
Let's set the meeting.

917
01:13:38,992 --> 01:13:42,039
Get our informers to find out
where it's going to be held.

918
01:13:44,563 --> 01:13:48,393
Now we insist it's a public place.
A bar, a restaurant.

919
01:13:48,436 --> 01:13:52,092
Some place where there's
people, so I feel safe.

920
01:13:54,964 --> 01:13:57,967
They're gonna search me
when I meet them, right?

921
01:13:58,011 --> 01:13:59,708
So I can't have
a weapon on me then.

922
01:14:03,756 --> 01:14:08,630
But if Clemenza can figure way to
have a weapon planted there for me

923
01:14:13,635 --> 01:14:14,984
then I'll kill them both.

924
01:14:18,031 --> 01:14:19,598
[CLEMENZA CHUCKLING]

925
01:14:20,860 --> 01:14:22,514
[LAUGHING]

926
01:14:22,557 --> 01:14:24,385
[ALL LAUGHING]

927
01:14:26,474 --> 01:14:27,867
SONNY: Hey.

928
01:14:27,910 --> 01:14:29,825
What are you gonna do?

929
01:14:29,869 --> 01:14:32,785
Nice college boy, huh? Didn't want to
get mixed up in the family business.

930
01:14:32,828 --> 01:14:34,352
Now you want to gun down
a police captain,

931
01:14:34,395 --> 01:14:36,528
why, because he slapped you
in the face a little bit, huh?

932
01:14:36,571 --> 01:14:38,965
What do you think, this is the army
where you shoot them a mile away?

933
01:14:39,008 --> 01:14:40,575
You got to get close like
this, bada bing!

934
01:14:40,619 --> 01:14:43,187
You blow their brains all over
your nice Ivy League suit.

935
01:14:43,230 --> 01:14:46,364
Come here.
You're taking this very personal.

936
01:14:46,407 --> 01:14:49,845
Tom, this is business, and this man
is taking it very, very personal.

937
01:14:49,889 --> 01:14:51,586
Where does it say
you can't kill a cop?

938
01:14:52,457 --> 01:14:53,719
Come on, Mikey...

939
01:14:53,762 --> 01:14:55,721
Tom, wait a minute.
I'm talking about a cop

940
01:14:55,764 --> 01:14:57,288
that's mixed up in drugs.

941
01:14:57,331 --> 01:15:00,421
I'm talking about
a dishonest cop.

942
01:15:00,465 --> 01:15:04,904
A crooked cop who got mixed up in the
rackets and got what was coming to him.

943
01:15:04,947 --> 01:15:08,299
That's a terrific story. We have
newspaper people on the payroll,

944
01:15:08,342 --> 01:15:09,474
don't we, Tom?

945
01:15:10,953 --> 01:15:12,868
They might like
a story like that.

946
01:15:12,912 --> 01:15:14,740
They might.
They just might.

947
01:15:18,483 --> 01:15:21,921
It's not personal, Sonny.
It's strictly business.

948
01:15:25,185 --> 01:15:26,839
CLEMENZA: It's as cold
as they come.

949
01:15:26,882 --> 01:15:30,451
Impossible to trace,
so you don't worry about prints, Mike.

950
01:15:30,495 --> 01:15:33,280
I put a special tape on
the trigger and the butt.

951
01:15:33,324 --> 01:15:34,499
Here. Try it.

952
01:15:46,728 --> 01:15:48,687
What's the matter?
Is the trigger too tight?

953
01:15:51,907 --> 01:15:53,518
[CHUCKLING] I don't know.
My ears!

954
01:15:53,561 --> 01:15:55,389
Yeah, I left it noisy.

955
01:15:55,433 --> 01:15:59,306
That way it scares away any
pain-in-the-ass innocent bystanders away.

956
01:15:59,350 --> 01:16:01,395
All right. You've shot them both.
Now what do you do?

957
01:16:04,224 --> 01:16:06,531
Sit down,
finish my dinner.

958
01:16:06,574 --> 01:16:08,359
Come on, kid.
Don't fool around.

959
01:16:08,402 --> 01:16:11,927
Just let your hand drop to your
side and let the gun slip out.

960
01:16:11,971 --> 01:16:14,147
Everybody will still think
you've got it.

961
01:16:14,191 --> 01:16:16,454
They're gonna be staring
at your face, Mike,

962
01:16:16,497 --> 01:16:19,370
so walk out of the place
real fast, but you don't run.

963
01:16:19,413 --> 01:16:20,893
Don't look nobody
directly in the eye,

964
01:16:20,936 --> 01:16:22,895
but don't look away either.

965
01:16:22,938 --> 01:16:24,940
Hey, they're gonna be scared
stiff of you, believe me,

966
01:16:24,984 --> 01:16:26,203
so don't worry
about nothing.

967
01:16:28,466 --> 01:16:30,337
You know, you're gonna
turn out all right.

968
01:16:30,381 --> 01:16:32,818
You'll take a vacation,
nobody knows where,

969
01:16:32,861 --> 01:16:34,123
and we're gonna
catch the hell.

970
01:16:35,560 --> 01:16:37,388
How bad do you think
it's gonna be?

971
01:16:37,431 --> 01:16:39,520
Pretty goddamn bad.

972
01:16:39,564 --> 01:16:42,697
Probably all the other families
will line up against us.

973
01:16:42,741 --> 01:16:45,613
But it's all right. These things
have to happen every five years or so.

974
01:16:45,657 --> 01:16:46,832
Ten years...

975
01:16:46,875 --> 01:16:48,312
How else do you get rid
of the bad blood.

976
01:16:48,355 --> 01:16:51,010
Been 10 years
since the last one.

977
01:16:51,053 --> 01:16:52,838
You know, you got to stop
them at the beginning.

978
01:16:52,881 --> 01:16:55,057
Like they should have
