1430
02:06:21,543 --> 02:06:23,545
VITO: Don Barzini,
I want to thank you

1431
02:06:23,588 --> 02:06:27,505
for helping me organize
this meeting in a day,

1432
02:06:27,549 --> 02:06:32,293
and the other heads of the five
families from New York and New Jersey.

1433
02:06:34,077 --> 02:06:37,254
Carmine Cuneo
from the Bronx,

1434
02:06:37,298 --> 02:06:40,692
and from Brooklyn

1435
02:06:42,346 --> 02:06:44,392
Philip Tattaglia.

1436
02:06:46,045 --> 02:06:49,005
And from Staten Island

1437
02:06:49,048 --> 02:06:52,574
we have with us
Victor Strachi.

1438
02:06:52,617 --> 02:06:58,275
And the other associates that came as
far as from California and Kansas City

1439
02:06:58,319 --> 02:07:02,018
and all the other territories
of the country. Thank you.

1440
02:07:08,764 --> 02:07:10,940
How did things
ever get so far?

1441
02:07:12,289 --> 02:07:13,899
I don't know.

1442
02:07:15,988 --> 02:07:19,427
It was so unfortunate,
so unnecessary.

1443
02:07:22,604 --> 02:07:26,172
Tattaglia lost a son,
and I lost a son.

1444
02:07:28,479 --> 02:07:32,004
We're quits.
And if Tattaglia agrees,

1445
02:07:32,048 --> 02:07:37,445
then I'm willing to let things
go on the way they were before.

1446
02:07:37,488 --> 02:07:41,187
We're all grateful to Don
Corleone for calling this meeting.

1447
02:07:41,231 --> 02:07:43,886
We all know him
as a man of his word.

1448
02:07:43,929 --> 02:07:46,454
A modest man who
always listens to reason.

1449
02:07:46,497 --> 02:07:50,849
Yes, Don Barzini.
He's too modest.

1450
02:07:50,893 --> 02:07:53,852
He had all the judges and
politicians in his pocket.

1451
02:07:55,114 --> 02:07:58,074
