an accommodation?

1453
02:08:01,947 --> 02:08:03,819
All of you know me here.

1454
02:08:05,299 --> 02:08:10,391
When did I ever refuse,
except one time? And why?

1455
02:08:12,088 --> 02:08:13,655
Because I believe

1456
02:08:13,698 --> 02:08:17,920
this drug business is gonna
destroy us in the years to come.

1457
02:08:17,963 --> 02:08:22,403
I mean, it's not like gambling
or liquor or even women,

1458
02:08:22,446 --> 02:08:24,753
which is something that
most people want nowadays,

1459
02:08:24,796 --> 02:08:28,409
but is forbidden to them by
the pezzonovante of the Church.

1460
02:08:28,452 --> 02:08:30,149
Even the police departments

1461
02:08:30,193 --> 02:08:33,196
that have helped us in the past
with gambling and other things

1462
02:08:33,239 --> 02:08:34,502
are going to refuse to help us

1463
02:08:34,545 --> 02:08:37,592
when it comes to narcotics.

1464
02:08:37,635 --> 02:08:42,814
And I believed that then
and I believe that now.

1465
02:08:42,858 --> 02:08:45,034
Times have changed.

1466
02:08:45,077 --> 02:08:49,952
It's not like the old days,
when we can do anything we want.

1467
02:08:49,995 --> 02:08:52,824
A refusal is not
the act of a friend.

1468
02:08:52,868 --> 02:08:56,828
If Don Corleone had all the judges
and politicians in New York,

1469
02:08:56,872 --> 02:08:58,700
then he must share them

1470
02:08:58,743 --> 02:09:03,966
or let others use them. He must let
us draw the water from the well.

1471
02:09:04,009 --> 02:09:07,622
Certainly he can present
a bill for such services.

1472
02:09:07,665 --> 02:09:10,581
After all,
we're not communists.

1473
02:09:10,625 --> 02:09:13,323
[ALL LAUGH]

1474
02:09:13,367 --> 02:09:16,587
I also don't believe
in drugs.

1475
02:09:16,631 --> 02:09:18,850
For years I paid
my people extra,

1476
02:09:18,894 --> 02:09:21,505
so they wouldn't
do that kind of business.

1477
02:09:21,549 --> 02:09:24,682
Somebody says to them
and says, "I have powders.

1478
02:09:24,726 --> 02:09:28,338
"If you put up
3-4,000 dollar investment,

1479
02:09:28,382 --> 02:09:30,949
"we can make
50,000 distributing."

1480
02:09:32,255 --> 02:09:33,909
So they can't resist.

1481
02:09:33,952 --> 02:09:38,261
I want to control it as a
business, to keep it respectable.

1482
02:09:38,304 --> 02:09:40,437
I don't want it
near schools,

1483
02:09:40,481 --> 02:09:42,396
I don't want it
sold to children.

1484
02:09:43,135 --> 02:09:46,225
That's an infamia.

1485
02:09:46,269 --> 02:09:50,316
In my city we would keep the traffic
and the dark people, the colored.

1486
02:09:50,360 --> 02:09:53,232
They're animals anyway,
so let them lose their souls.

1487
02:10:00,152 --> 02:10:03,678
I hoped that we could come
here and reason together.

1488
02:10:05,114 --> 02:10:06,550
And as a reasonable man,

1489
02:10:06,594 --> 02:10:08,596
I'm willing to do
whatever is necessary

1490
02:10:08,639 --> 02:10:12,295
to find a peaceful solution
to this problem.

1491
02:10:12,338 --> 02:10:14,340
Then we are agreed.

1492
02:10:14,384 --> 02:10:16,821
The traffic in drugs will be
permitted, but controlled.

1493
02:10:16,865 --> 02:10:21,347
And Don Corleone will give us protection
in the east, and there will be the peace.

1494
02:10:21,391 --> 02:10:25,177
But I must have strict
assurance from Corleone.

1495
02:10:25,221 --> 02:10:28,529
As time goes by and his
position becomes stronger,

1496
02:10:28,572 --> 02:10:31,314
will he attempt
any individual vendetta?

1497
02:10:31,357 --> 02:10:33,055
BARZINI: Look, we are all
reasonable men here.

1498
02:10:33,098 --> 02:10:36,493
We don't have to give
assurances as if we were lawyers.

1499
02:10:36,537 --> 02:10:39,453
You talk about
vengeance.

1500
02:10:39,496 --> 02:10:42,194
Is vengeance gonna
bring your son back to you?

1501
02:10:42,847 --> 02:10:44,370
Or my boy to me?

1502
02:10:45,546 --> 02:10:47,852
I forgo the vengeance
of my son.

1503
02:10:51,116 --> 02:10:53,031
But I have
selfish reasons.

1504
02:10:55,773 --> 02:10:59,255
My youngest son was forced
to leave this country

1505
02:11:01,170 --> 02:11:03,389
because of this
Sollozzo business.

1506
02:11:03,955 --> 02:11:05,566
All right.

1507
02:11:05,609 --> 02:11:09,265
And I have to make arrangements
to bring him back here safely.

1508
02:11:09,308 --> 02:11:11,485
Cleared of all these
false charges.

1509
02:11:13,356 --> 02:11:15,314
But I'm
a superstitious man.

1510
02:11:16,664 --> 02:11:19,144
And if some unlucky accident
should befall him,

1511
02:11:19,188 --> 02:11:21,886
if he should get shot in the
head by a police officer,

1512
02:11:23,322 --> 02:11:26,935
or if he should hang himself
in his jail cell,

1513
02:11:26,978 --> 02:11:29,503
or if he's struck
by a bolt of lightning,

1514
02:11:31,113 --> 02:11:34,159
then I'm going to blame some
of the people in this room.

1515
02:11:36,248 --> 02:11:38,120
And that I do not forgive.

1516
02:11:41,210 --> 02:11:43,560
But, that aside

1517
02:11:46,694 --> 02:11:48,609
let me say that I swear

1518
02:11:50,654 --> 02:11:53,875
on the souls
of my grandchildren,

1519
02:11:53,918 --> 02:11:57,313
that I will not be the one to break
the peace we've made here today.

1520
02:12:23,774 --> 02:12:25,776
When I meet
with the Tattaglia people,

1521
02:12:25,820 --> 02:12:29,258
Should I insist that all his drug
middlemen have clean records?

1522
02:12:29,301 --> 02:12:31,086
Mention it.
Don't insist.

1523
02:12:33,436 --> 02:12:36,004
Barzini is a man who will
know that without being told.

1524
02:12:37,179 --> 02:12:38,310
You mean Tattaglia.

1525
02:12:39,921 --> 02:12:41,618
Tattaglia's a pimp.

1526
02:12:43,054 --> 02:12:45,230
He could never
have outfought Santino.

1527
02:12:48,582 --> 02:12:50,409
But I didn't know
until this day

1528
02:12:50,453 --> 02:12:54,152
that it was Barzini
all along..

1529
02:13:09,472 --> 02:13:10,865
Come on, Nancy.

1530
02:13:12,910 --> 02:13:15,391
Keep together,
everyone. Brian.

1531
02:13:16,871 --> 02:13:18,263
Okay, all right.

1532
02:13:31,581 --> 02:13:33,278
How long
have you been back?

1533
02:13:34,584 --> 02:13:35,803
I've been back a year.

1534
02:13:37,935 --> 02:13:38,936
Longer than that, I think.

1535
02:13:42,766 --> 02:13:44,072
It's good to see you, Kay.

1536
02:13:50,992 --> 02:13:53,342
Hi, Ms. Adams.
[CYCLE BELL TRILLS]

1537
02:13:53,908 --> 02:13:55,910
[DOG BARKING]

1538
02:13:55,953 --> 02:13:57,738
I'm working for
my father now, Kay.

1539
02:14:01,002 --> 02:14:03,961
He's been sick.
Very sick.

1540
02:14:05,528 --> 02:14:07,530
But you're not
like him, Michael.

1541
02:14:07,573 --> 02:14:10,315
I thought you weren't going to
become a man like your father.

1542
02:14:10,359 --> 02:14:11,577
That's what you told me.

1543
02:14:13,318 --> 02:14:16,060
My father is no different
than any other powerful man.

1544
02:14:16,104 --> 02:14:17,671
[SCOFFS]

1545
02:14:17,714 --> 02:14:21,109
Any man who's responsible
for other people.

1546
02:14:22,371 --> 02:14:24,808
Like a senator
or president.

1547
02:14:24,852 --> 02:14:26,114
You know
how naive you sound.

1548
02:14:26,157 --> 02:14:27,506
Why?

1549
02:14:27,550 --> 02:14:29,857
Senators and presidents
don't have men killed.

1550
02:14:31,423 --> 02:14:33,164
Oh.

1551
02:14:33,208 --> 02:14:36,559
Who's being naive, Kay?

1552
02:14:36,602 --> 02:14:39,867
Kay, my father's way of doing
things is over. It's finished.

1553
02:14:39,910 --> 02:14:41,216
Even he knows that.

1554
02:14:42,347 --> 02:14:43,914
I mean, in five years

1555
02:14:43,958 --> 02:14:46,395
the Corleone family is going
to be completely legitimate.

1556
02:14:48,702 --> 02:14:52,618
Trust me. That's all I can tell
you about my business. Kay...

1557
02:14:53,968 --> 02:14:57,145
Michael, why did
you come here? Why?

1558
02:14:57,188 --> 02:14:59,234
[SOBS]

1559
02:14:59,277 --> 02:15:03,325
What do you want with me after all this
time? I've been calling and writing.

1560
02:15:03,368 --> 02:15:05,370
I came because I need you.

1561
02:15:05,414 --> 02:15:06,850
Because I care for you.

1562
02:15:06,894 --> 02:15:08,156
Please stop it, Michael.

1563
02:15:08,199 --> 02:15:10,767
Because...
I want you to marry me.

1564
02:15:12,464 --> 02:15:13,639
It's too late.
It's too late.

1565
02:15:13,683 --> 02:15:16,773
Please, Kay...

1566
02:15:16,817 --> 02:15:20,734
I'll do anything you ask. Anything
to make up for what's happened to us.

1567
02:15:22,561 --> 02:15:24,912
Because
that's important, Kay.

1568
02:15:24,955 --> 02:15:28,219
Because what's
important is that

1569
02:15:28,263 --> 02:15:31,657
we have each other.
That we have a life together.

1570
02:15:33,094 --> 02:15:34,791
That we have children.

1571
02:15:34,835 --> 02:15:36,053
Our children.

1572
02:15:37,315 --> 02:15:39,578
Kay, I need you.

1573
02:15:41,450 --> 02:15:43,060
And I love you.

1574
02:16:05,517 --> 02:16:09,130
TESSIO: Barzini's people chisel my
territory and we do nothing about it!

1575
02:16:09,173 --> 02:16:11,523
Pretty soon I there won't be one
place in Brooklyn I can hang my hat!

1576
02:16:11,567 --> 02:16:13,482
MICHAEL: Just be patient.

1577
02:16:13,525 --> 02:16:15,963
TESSIO: I'm not asking you for help,
Mike Just take off the handcuffs.

1578
02:16:16,006 --> 02:16:17,268
MICHAEL: Be patient.

1579
02:16:17,312 --> 02:16:19,227
CARLO: We got to
protect ourselves.

1580
02:16:19,270 --> 02:16:21,229
Give me a chance
to recruit some new men.

1581
02:16:21,272 --> 02:16:22,926
MICHAEL: No.

1582
02:16:22,970 --> 02:16:25,581
I don't want to give Barzini
an excuse to start fighting.

1583
02:16:25,624 --> 02:16:27,322
TESSIO: Mike, you're wrong.

1584
02:16:28,149 --> 02:16:30,455
CLEMENZA: Don Corleone...

1585
02:16:30,499 --> 02:16:32,153
You once said that
the day would come

1586
02:16:32,196 --> 02:16:34,633
when Tessio and me
could form our own family.

1587
02:16:34,677 --> 02:16:36,592
Till today
I would never think of it.

1588
02:16:36,635 --> 02:16:38,376
I must ask
your permission.

1589
02:16:39,769 --> 02:16:42,511
Michael is now
head of the family

1590
02:16:42,554 --> 02:16:45,470
and if he gives his permission,
then you have my blessing.

1591
02:16:46,907 --> 02:16:49,344
After we make
the move to Nevada

1592
02:16:49,387 --> 02:16:52,477
you can break off from the
Corleone family and go on your own.

1593
02:16:52,521 --> 02:16:53,783
After we make
the move to Nevada.

1594
02:16:53,827 --> 02:16:55,089
TESSIO:
How long will that be?

1595
02:16:56,830 --> 02:16:58,135
Six months.

1596
02:16:58,179 --> 02:17:01,573
Forgive me, Godfather,
but with you gone,

1597
02:17:01,617 --> 02:17:04,576
me and Pete will come under
Barzini's thumb sooner or later.

1598
02:17:04,620 --> 02:17:06,796
And I hate that
goddamn Barzini.

1599
02:17:06,840 --> 02:17:10,234
In six months' time there will
be nothing left to build on.

1600
02:17:10,278 --> 02:17:12,062
Do you have faith
in my judgment?

1601
02:17:12,106 --> 02:17:13,237
Yes.

1602
02:17:13,281 --> 02:17:14,760
Do I have your loyalty?

1603
02:17:14,804 --> 02:17:16,240
Yes, always, Godfather.

1604
02:17:16,284 --> 02:17:17,807
Then be a friend to Michael.

1605
02:17:18,373 --> 02:17:19,722
Do as he says.

1606
02:17:24,466 --> 02:17:26,294
There are things
being negotiated now

1607
02:17:26,337 --> 02:17:29,819
that are gonna solve all your problems
and answer all your questions.

1608
02:17:29,863 --> 02:17:31,386
That's all
I can tell you now.

1609
02:17:33,040 --> 02:17:35,694
Carlo, you grew up
in Nevada.

1610
02:17:35,738 --> 02:17:38,001
When we make our move there,
you'll be my right-hand man.

1611
02:17:39,220 --> 02:17:40,656
Tom Hagen
is no longer consigliere.

1612
02:17:41,700 --> 02:17:44,051
He'll be our lawyer in Vegas.

1613
02:17:44,094 --> 02:17:46,662
That's no reflection on Tom,
just how I want it.

1614
02:17:46,705 --> 02:17:48,620
Besides, if I ever need help,

1615
02:17:48,664 --> 02:17:50,622
who's a better consigliere
than my father?

1616
02:17:50,666 --> 02:17:51,928
Well, that's it.

1617
02:18:11,426 --> 02:18:12,514
Thank you, Papa.

1618
02:18:12,557 --> 02:18:13,950
I'm happy
for you, Carlo.

1619
02:18:15,430 --> 02:18:18,215
Mike... Why am I out?

1620
02:18:19,782 --> 02:18:21,871
You're not
a wartime consigliere, Tom.

1621
02:18:23,786 --> 02:18:26,354
Things may get rough
with the move we're trying.

1622
02:18:27,007 --> 02:18:28,095
Tom.

1623
02:18:33,491 --> 02:18:35,929
I advised Michael.

1624
02:18:35,972 --> 02:18:38,844
I never thought
you were a bad consigliere.

1625
02:18:38,888 --> 02:18:42,979
I thought Santino was a bad
Don, rest in peace.

1626
02:18:44,415 --> 02:18:48,637
Michael has all my
confidence, just as you do.

1627
02:18:48,680 --> 02:18:53,642
But there are reasons why you must have
no part in what is going to happen.

1628
02:18:54,686 --> 02:18:56,340
Maybe I could help.

1629
02:18:56,384 --> 02:18:57,689
You're out, Tom.

1630
02:19:07,873 --> 02:19:09,353
[DOOR CLOSING]

1631
02:19:46,869 --> 02:19:49,698
I can't get over the way
your face looks.

1632
02:19:49,741 --> 02:19:51,265
It really looks good!

1633
02:19:51,308 --> 02:19:53,789
This doctor did some job.
Who talked you into it?

1634
02:19:53,832 --> 02:19:55,921
Kay? Hey, hey, hey!
Wait. Hey, hey.

1635
02:19:55,965 --> 02:19:57,880
Leave them out here.
We'll deal with them later.

1636
02:19:57,923 --> 02:20:00,230
He's tired and wants
to clean up. All right now.

1637
02:20:00,274 --> 02:20:01,623
Let me open the door,
all right?

1638
02:20:03,973 --> 02:20:06,454
[PLAYING FOR HE'S A JOLLY GOOD FELLOW]

1639
02:20:08,673 --> 02:20:11,111
Hello, Mike!
Welcome to Las Vegas!

1640
02:20:11,154 --> 02:20:14,418
All for you, kid! Huh?
It's all his idea, right?

1641
02:20:14,462 --> 02:20:15,767
JOHNNY: Your brother Freddy.

1642
02:20:15,811 --> 02:20:17,073
FREDO: Girls?
[BOTH LAUGH]

1643
02:20:20,816 --> 02:20:23,862
I'll be right back.
You keep them occupied.

1644
02:20:23,906 --> 02:20:24,994
Atta boy, huh?

1645
02:20:25,038 --> 02:20:27,301
Anything you want, kid,
anything. Huh?

1646
02:20:27,344 --> 02:20:28,606
Who are the girls?

1647
02:20:29,955 --> 02:20:31,957
That's for you
to find out.

1648
02:20:32,001 --> 02:20:33,350
Get rid of them, Fredo.

1649
02:20:34,960 --> 02:20:36,875
Hey, Mike...

1650
02:20:36,919 --> 02:20:39,704
Fredo, I'm here on business.
I leave tomorrow. Now get rid of them.

1651
02:20:39,748 --> 02:20:42,359
I'm tired.
Get rid of the band too.

1652
02:20:48,365 --> 02:20:51,325
Hey, just take off.
Come on. Take off. Let's go.

1653
02:20:51,368 --> 02:20:53,457
Come on. Hey, that's it.
Hey, Angelo.

1654
02:20:54,719 --> 02:20:57,592
Come on, let's go.
Hey, come on! Scram!

1655
02:20:59,376 --> 02:21:01,509
Come on, honey. Let's go.
I don't know, Johnny.

1656
02:21:01,552 --> 02:21:02,901
What the hell's
the matter with him?

1657
02:21:02,945 --> 02:21:04,816
I'm sorry.
Sorry... Sorry.

1658
02:21:06,209 --> 02:21:08,733
I don't know.
He's tired.

1659
02:21:10,039 --> 02:21:11,084
[SIGHS]

1660
02:21:14,348 --> 02:21:15,740
[DOOR CLOSING]

1661
02:21:15,784 --> 02:21:17,351
What happened
to Moe Greene?

1662
02:21:18,961 --> 02:21:20,397
He said he had
some business.

1663
02:21:20,441 --> 02:21:23,313
He said to give him a call
when the party started.

1664
02:21:23,357 --> 02:21:25,228
Well, give him a call.
[PATS ON BACK]

1665
02:21:26,664 --> 02:21:28,057
Johnny, how are you?

1666
02:21:28,101 --> 02:21:29,928
Hello, Mike.
Nice to see you again.

1667
02:21:29,972 --> 02:21:31,016
MICHAEL:
We're proud of you.

1668
02:21:31,060 --> 02:21:32,192
JOHNNY: Thanks, Mike.

1669
02:21:32,235 --> 02:21:34,498
Sit down, Johnny,
I want to talk to you.

1670
02:21:34,542 --> 02:21:35,847
The Don is proud
too, Johnny.

1671
02:21:35,891 --> 02:21:39,024
Well, I owe it
all to him.

1672
02:21:39,068 --> 02:21:41,026
Well, he knows
how grateful you are.

1673
02:21:41,070 --> 02:21:44,204
That's why he'd like
to ask a favor of you.

1674
02:21:44,247 --> 02:21:45,640
Mike, what can I do?

1675
02:21:47,468 --> 02:21:49,948
The Corleone family is thinking
of giving up all its interests

1676
02:21:49,992 --> 02:21:53,604
in the olive oil business
and settling out here.

1677
02:21:53,648 --> 02:21:56,346
Now Moe Greene will sell
us his share of the casino

1678
02:21:56,390 --> 02:21:59,132
and the hotel, so it could
completely be owned by the family.

1679
02:21:59,175 --> 02:22:01,960
Tom! Hey, Mike,
are you sure about that?

1680
02:22:02,004 --> 02:22:04,963
Moe loves the business. He never
said nothing to me about selling.

1681
02:22:05,007 --> 02:22:07,140
Yeah, I'll make him an offer
he can't refuse.

1682
02:22:08,967 --> 02:22:10,230
See, Johnny...

1683
02:22:11,492 --> 02:22:13,146
See, we figure
that entertainment

1684
02:22:13,189 --> 02:22:15,800
will be a big factor in
drawing gamblers to the casino.

1685
02:22:15,844 --> 02:22:17,498
And we hope
you'll sign a contract

1686
02:22:17,541 --> 02:22:19,282
to appear
five times a year.

1687
02:22:22,546 --> 02:22:27,160
Perhaps convince some of your
friends in the movies to do the same.

1688
02:22:28,378 --> 02:22:29,640
We're counting on you.

1689
02:22:32,556 --> 02:22:35,168
Sure, Mike.
I'll do anything for my godfather.

1690
02:22:35,211 --> 02:22:37,082
You know that.
Good.

1691
02:22:39,259 --> 02:22:43,872
Hey, Mike! Hello, fellows.
Everybody's here. Freddy, Tom.

1692
02:22:43,915 --> 02:22:45,265
Good to see you, Mike.

1693
02:22:45,308 --> 02:22:46,570
How are you, Moe?
All right.

1694
02:22:46,614 --> 02:22:47,658
Did you get
everything you want?

1695
02:22:47,702 --> 02:22:49,269
The chef cooked
for you special,

1696
02:22:49,312 --> 02:22:51,793
the dancers will kick your tongue
out and you credit is good!

1697
02:22:51,836 --> 02:22:54,317
Draw chips for everybody in the
room so they can play on the house.

1698
02:22:58,103 --> 02:22:59,714
My credit good enough
to buy you out?

1699
02:22:59,757 --> 02:23:01,759
[LAUGHING]

1700
02:23:02,499 --> 02:23:03,674
Buy me out?

1701
02:23:04,458 --> 02:23:07,112
The casino, the hotel.

1702
02:23:07,156 --> 02:23:10,115
The Corleone family
wants to buy you out.

1703
02:23:10,159 --> 02:23:12,988
The Corleone family
wants to buy me out?

1704
02:23:13,031 --> 02:23:15,599
No, I buy you out.
You don't buy me out.

1705
02:23:15,643 --> 02:23:19,124
Your casino loses money.
Maybe we can do better.

1706
02:23:19,168 --> 02:23:20,604
You think I'm skimming
off the top, Mike?

1707
02:23:22,302 --> 02:23:23,346
You're unlucky.

1708
02:23:25,000 --> 02:23:27,785
[CHUCKLING]

1709
02:23:27,829 --> 02:23:30,353
You goddamn Guineas
really make me laugh.

1710
02:23:30,397 --> 02:23:32,094
I do you a favor
and take Freddy in

1711
02:23:32,137 --> 02:23:33,487
when you're having
a bad time,

1712
02:23:33,530 --> 02:23:36,316
and now you try
to push me out! Wait a minute.

1713
02:23:36,359 --> 02:23:39,884
You took Freddy in because the
Corleone family bankrolled your Casino,

1714
02:23:39,928 --> 02:23:43,236
because the Molinari family on
the coast guaranteed his safety.

1715
02:23:43,279 --> 02:23:45,194
Now we're talking business.
Let's talk business.

1716
02:23:45,238 --> 02:23:46,674
Yeah, let's talk
business, Mike.

1717
02:23:46,717 --> 02:23:48,371
First of all,
you're all done.

1718
02:23:48,415 --> 02:23:50,678
The Corleone family don't have
that kind of muscle anymore.

1719
02:23:50,721 --> 02:23:52,680
The Godfather is sick, right?

1720
02:23:52,723 --> 02:23:55,073
You're getting chased out of New York
by Barzini and the other families.

1721
02:23:55,117 --> 02:23:56,553
What do you think is going on?

1722
02:23:56,597 --> 02:23:59,164
You think you can come to
my hotel and take over?

1723
02:23:59,208 --> 02:24:04,169
I talked to Barzini. I can make a
deal with him and still keep my hotel!

1724
02:24:04,213 --> 02:24:07,782
Is that why you slapped my
brother around in public?

1725
02:24:07,825 --> 02:24:12,569
Ah, that was nothing, Mike.
Now, Moe didn't mean nothing by that.

1726
02:24:12,613 --> 02:24:15,050
Sure he flies off the handle
once in a while,

1727
02:24:15,093 --> 02:24:17,052
but Moe and me we're good
friends, right Moe, huh?

1728
02:24:17,095 --> 02:24:19,054
I've got a business to run.

1729
02:24:19,097 --> 02:24:21,883
I've got to kick asses
sometimes to make it run right.

1730
02:24:21,926 --> 02:24:23,319
We had a little argument,
Freddy and I,

1731
02:24:23,363 --> 02:24:24,755
so I had
to straighten him out.

1732
02:24:25,930 --> 02:24:27,280
You straightened
my brother out?

1733
02:24:28,629 --> 02:24:31,371
He was banging cocktail
waitresses two at a time!

1734
02:24:31,414 --> 02:24:34,112
Players couldn't get a drink at
the table. What's wrong with you?

1735
02:24:40,162 --> 02:24:43,731
I leave for New York tomorrow.
Think about a price.

1736
02:24:43,774 --> 02:24:45,776
[DRINK SPILLING]
MOE: Son of a bitch!

1737
02:24:45,820 --> 02:24:48,692
Do you know who I am?
I'm Moe Greene!

1738
02:24:48,736 --> 02:24:51,129
I made my bones when you were
going out with cheerleaders.

1739
02:24:51,173 --> 02:24:53,393
Wait a minute, Moe.
I got an idea.

1740
02:24:54,698 --> 02:24:56,918
Tom, Tom,
you're the consigliere.

1741
02:24:56,961 --> 02:24:58,311
You can talk to the Don...
You can explain...

1742
02:24:58,354 --> 02:25:00,225
Just a minute now.

1743
02:25:00,269 --> 02:25:03,707
Don is semi-retired and Mike is in
charge of the family business now.

1744
02:25:03,751 --> 02:25:06,536
If you have anything to
say, say it to Michael.

1745
02:25:10,497 --> 02:25:12,542
[DOOR SLAMMING]

1746
02:25:12,586 --> 02:25:15,937
Mike, you don't come to Las Vegas and
talk to a man like Moe Greene like that!

1747
02:25:17,678 --> 02:25:18,809
Fredo...

1748
02:25:20,158 --> 02:25:22,552
You're my older brother,
and I love you.

1749
02:25:24,380 --> 02:25:27,775
But don't ever take sides with
anyone against the family again.

1750
02:25:29,820 --> 02:25:30,908
Ever.

1751
02:25:39,090 --> 02:25:42,050
I have to see my father and his
people, so have dinner without me.

1752
02:25:42,093 --> 02:25:43,443
Oh, Michael.

1753
02:25:44,966 --> 02:25:46,924
This weekend we'll go out.
Mmm.

1754
02:25:46,968 --> 02:25:49,579
We'll go to the city, we'll see a
show and we'll have dinner. I promise.

1755
02:25:50,101 --> 02:25:51,146
Mmm.

1756
02:25:57,239 --> 02:26:00,242
Oh, Michael., Michael,
your sister wants to ask you something.

1757
02:26:00,285 --> 02:26:01,374
Let her ask.

1758
02:26:01,417 --> 02:26:02,940
No, she's afraid to.

1759
02:26:02,984 --> 02:26:05,552
Connie and Carlo want you to
be godfather to their boy.

1760
02:26:05,595 --> 02:26:07,467
We'll see.
Will you?

1761
02:26:07,510 --> 02:26:09,338
Let me think about it.
We'll see. Come on.

1762
02:26:16,519 --> 02:26:17,520
So...

1763
02:26:18,608 --> 02:26:21,655
Barzini will move
against you first.

1764
02:26:21,698 --> 02:26:25,006
He'll set up a meeting with
someone that you absolutely trust.

1765
02:26:26,137 --> 02:26:27,791
Guaranteeing your safety.

1766
02:26:29,358 --> 02:26:31,969
And at that meeting
you'll be assassinated.

1767
02:26:37,322 --> 02:26:39,803
I like to drink wine
more than I used to.

1768
02:26:41,631 --> 02:26:43,894
Anyway,
I'm drinking more.

1769
02:26:43,938 --> 02:26:45,330
It's good for you, Pop.

1770
02:26:50,335 --> 02:26:51,380
I don't know.

1771
02:26:53,774 --> 02:26:55,602
Your wife and children,
are you happy with them?

1772
02:26:57,517 --> 02:26:58,605
Very happy.

1773
02:26:59,519 --> 02:27:02,304
That's good.

1774
02:27:02,347 --> 02:27:07,265
I hope you don't mind the way I keep
going over this Barzini business.

1775
02:27:07,309 --> 02:27:09,224
No, not at all.

1776
02:27:09,267 --> 02:27:11,705
It's an old habit.

1777
02:27:11,748 --> 02:27:14,229
I spend my life trying
not to be careless.

1778
02:27:16,231 --> 02:27:19,234
Women and children can be
careless, but not men.

1779
02:27:22,542 --> 02:27:23,760
How's your boy?

1780
02:27:24,326 --> 02:27:25,501
He's good.

1781
02:27:25,545 --> 02:27:27,677
You know, he looks
more like you every day.

1782
02:27:30,985 --> 02:27:33,466
He's smarter than I am.

1783
02:27:33,509 --> 02:27:35,250
Three years old and he can
read the funny papers.

1784
02:27:37,513 --> 02:27:39,123
Read the funny papers.

1785
02:27:44,738 --> 02:27:46,653
Uh...

1786
02:27:46,696 --> 02:27:49,351
I want you to arrange
to have a telephone man

1787
02:27:49,394 --> 02:27:52,572
check all the calls that go
in and out of here...

1788
02:27:52,615 --> 02:27:55,879
I did it already, Pop.
I took care of that. It could be anyone.

1789
02:27:55,923 --> 02:27:57,838
Oh, that's right. I forgot.

1790
02:28:01,885 --> 02:28:03,147
What's the matter?

1791
02:28:04,540 --> 02:28:05,846
What's bothering you?

1792
02:28:10,067 --> 02:28:12,461
I'll handle it.

1793
02:28:12,505 --> 02:28:14,507
I told you I can handle it,
I'll handle it.

1794
02:28:28,042 --> 02:28:31,175
I knew that Santino was gonna
have to go through all this.

1795
02:28:32,525 --> 02:28:34,265
And Fredo...

1796
02:28:34,309 --> 02:28:35,615
Well...

1797
02:28:36,877 --> 02:28:38,531
Fredo was, well...

1798
02:28:40,837 --> 02:28:43,623
But I never...
I never wanted this for you.

1799
02:28:45,973 --> 02:28:47,365
I worked my whole life.

1800
02:28:47,409 --> 02:28:51,065
I don't apologize
for take care of my family.

1801
02:28:51,108 --> 02:28:55,069
And I refused
to be a fool,

1802
02:28:55,112 --> 02:28:59,203
dancing on a string held
by all those big shots.

1803
02:29:01,249 --> 02:29:04,295
I don't apologize.
That's my life, but I thought that...

1804
02:29:06,341 --> 02:29:08,996
That when it was
your time,

1805
02:29:09,039 --> 02:29:11,520
that you would be
the one to hold the strings.

1806
02:29:13,304 --> 02:29:19,049
Senator Corleone.
Governor Corleone. Something.

1807
02:29:19,093 --> 02:29:20,529
Another pezzonovante.

1808
02:29:22,096 --> 02:29:23,358
Well...

1809
02:29:25,447 --> 02:29:27,101
[SIGHS]

1810
02:29:27,144 --> 02:29:31,018
Just wasn't enough time, Michael.
Wasn't enough time.

1811
02:29:31,061 --> 02:29:34,543
We'll get there, Pop.
We'll get there.

1812
02:29:35,588 --> 02:29:36,719
Hmm.

1813
02:29:39,417 --> 02:29:43,900
Now listen, whoever comes to
you with this Barzini meeting,

1814
02:29:43,944 --> 02:29:46,816
he's the traitor.
Don't forget that.

1815
02:30:04,007 --> 02:30:06,096
Can I hold it, please?

1816
02:30:21,242 --> 02:30:22,939
Can I water these?

1817
02:30:22,983 --> 02:30:25,159
Yes, go ahead.

1818
02:30:25,202 --> 02:30:27,944
Over here, over here.

1819
02:30:29,859 --> 02:30:32,340
Be careful.
You're spilling it.

1820
02:30:36,257 --> 02:30:37,824
[ANTHONY LAUGHING]

1821
02:30:38,825 --> 02:30:40,174
Anthony.

1822
02:30:40,217 --> 02:30:41,784
Come here, come here.

1823
02:30:43,830 --> 02:30:45,135
Come here.

1824
02:30:47,268 --> 02:30:49,879
That's it.
We'll put it right there.

1825
02:30:51,446 --> 02:30:52,708
[SIGHING]

1826
02:30:55,493 --> 02:30:58,105
I'll show you something.
Come here. Come here.

1827
02:30:59,802 --> 02:31:01,674
Stand there.

1828
02:31:05,373 --> 02:31:07,157
Give me an orange!

1829
02:31:10,421 --> 02:31:11,727
[GROWLING]

1830
02:31:13,816 --> 02:31:15,470
[ANTHONY CRYING]

1831
02:31:15,513 --> 02:31:17,037
[VITO LAUGHING]

1832
02:31:25,523 --> 02:31:27,264
That's a new trick.

1833
02:31:28,352 --> 02:31:30,659
You run in there.
Run in there.

1834
02:31:43,106 --> 02:31:44,238
[VITO LAUGHING]

1835
02:31:44,281 --> 02:31:46,196
ANTHONY: Where are you?

1836
02:31:51,593 --> 02:31:52,899
[COUGHING]

1837
02:31:54,117 --> 02:31:55,728
[ANTHONY LAUGHING]

1838
02:32:00,776 --> 02:32:02,560
[COUGHING CONTINUES]

1839
02:32:07,174 --> 02:32:08,784
[ANTHONY LAUGHING]

1840
02:32:16,139 --> 02:32:17,445
[ANTHONY EXCLAIMING]

1841
02:32:23,451 --> 02:32:25,235
[ANTHONY CHATTERING]

1842
02:32:35,680 --> 02:32:37,726
[BELL TOLLING]

1843
02:34:43,852 --> 02:34:45,593
Mike, can I
have a minute?

1844
02:34:56,386 --> 02:34:58,780
Barzini wants to
arrange a meeting.

1845
02:34:58,823 --> 02:35:02,001
He says we can straighten
out any of our problems.

1846
02:35:02,697 --> 02:35:03,785
You talked to him?

1847
02:35:03,828 --> 02:35:04,917
Yeah.

1848
02:35:06,309 --> 02:35:10,009
I can arrange security.
On my territory.

1849
02:35:13,142 --> 02:35:15,101
All right?

1850
02:35:15,144 --> 02:35:17,973
All right.

1851
02:35:33,249 --> 02:35:35,599
Do you know how they're
going to come at you?

1852
02:35:38,820 --> 02:35:42,432
They're arranging a meeting
in Brooklyn. Tessio's ground.

1853
02:35:44,608 --> 02:35:46,349
Where I'll be safe.

1854
02:35:58,666 --> 02:36:02,365
I always thought it would have
been Clemenza, not Tessio.

1855
02:36:02,409 --> 02:36:06,108
It's the smart move.
Tessio was always smarter.

1856
02:36:08,371 --> 02:36:09,633
But I'm going to wait.

1857
02:36:10,895 --> 02:36:12,419
After the baptism.

1858
02:36:15,248 --> 02:36:18,860
I've decided to be
godfather to Connie's baby.

1859
02:36:18,903 --> 02:36:23,212
And then I'll meet with
Don Barzini and Tattaglia.

1860
02:36:24,648 --> 02:36:26,911
All the heads
of the five families.

1861
02:36:30,785 --> 02:36:32,482
[ORGAN PLAYING]

1862
02:36:35,485 --> 02:36:37,009
[BABY CRYING]

1863
02:36:53,634 --> 02:36:55,375
[RECITING IN LATIN]

1864
02:37:25,883 --> 02:37:28,147
[RECITING CONTINUES]

1865
02:38:48,575 --> 02:38:51,447
PRIEST: Michael, do you believe
in God, the Father almighty,

1866
02:38:51,491 --> 02:38:53,536
Creator of Heaven and Earth?

1867
02:38:53,580 --> 02:38:55,234
I do.

1868
02:38:55,277 --> 02:38:58,367
PRIEST: Do you believe in Jesus Christ, His only Son, our Lord?

1869
02:38:58,411 --> 02:38:59,499
MICHAEL: I do.

1870
02:38:59,542 --> 02:39:01,501
Do you believe in the Holy Ghost,

1871
02:39:01,544 --> 02:39:03,546
the Holy Catholic Church?

1872
02:39:03,590 --> 02:39:05,026
I do.

1873
02:39:05,069 --> 02:39:07,246
[RECITING CONTINUES
IN LATIN]

1874
02:39:37,972 --> 02:39:39,582
[BABY CRYING]

1875
02:39:39,626 --> 02:39:41,280
[RECITING CONTINUES]

1876
02:40:10,613 --> 02:40:14,791
PRIEST: Michael Francis Rizzi,
do you renounce Satan?

1877
02:40:21,015 --> 02:40:22,277
I do renounce him.

1878
02:40:32,287 --> 02:40:33,288
And all his works?

1879
02:40:41,905 --> 02:40:43,124
[MUFFLED SHOUTING]

1880
02:40:47,389 --> 02:40:48,347
I do renounce them.

1881
02:40:50,131 --> 02:40:51,393
WOMAN: Oh, God!

1882
02:40:54,309 --> 02:40:56,616
PRIEST:
And all his pomps?

1883
02:40:56,659 --> 02:40:57,965
I do renounce them.

1884
02:41:13,763 --> 02:41:18,028
Michael Rizzi,
will you be baptized?

1885
02:41:18,072 --> 02:41:19,421
I will.

1886
02:41:19,465 --> 02:41:21,293
[RECITING IN LATIN]

1887
02:41:26,428 --> 02:41:29,170
Michael Rizzi,
go in peace,

1888
02:41:29,213 --> 02:41:32,478
and may the Lord
be with you. Amen.

1889
02:41:32,521 --> 02:41:34,393
[CHURCH BELLS RINGING]

1890
02:41:37,309 --> 02:41:39,223
[ALL CHATTERING]

1891
02:41:46,230 --> 02:41:48,145
Kay!

1892
02:41:48,189 --> 02:41:50,147
Kiss your godfather.

1893
02:42:02,072 --> 02:42:03,378
[INAUDIBLE]

1894
02:42:14,650 --> 02:42:18,741
Carlo, can't go to Vegas.
Something's come up.

1895
02:42:18,785 --> 02:42:20,482
Everybody has to
leave without us.

1896
02:42:20,526 --> 02:42:22,354
CONNIE: Mike,
it's our first vacation!

1897
02:42:22,397 --> 02:42:24,007
Connie, please.

1898
02:42:24,051 --> 02:42:26,488
Go back to the house, wait for my call.
It's important.

1899
02:42:26,532 --> 02:42:28,185
All right.

1900
02:42:28,229 --> 02:42:30,536
I'll only be
a couple of days.

1901
02:42:33,408 --> 02:42:34,931
[INDISTINCT CONVERSATION]

1902
02:42:46,900 --> 02:42:49,119
We're on our way
to Brooklyn.

1903
02:42:51,339 --> 02:42:53,776
I hope Mike can get us
a good deal tonight.

1904
02:42:53,820 --> 02:42:54,995
I'm sure he will.

1905
02:43:02,916 --> 02:43:08,356
Sal, Tom, the boss says he'll come in
a separate car, so you two go on ahead.

1906
02:43:08,400 --> 02:43:10,837
Hell, he can't do that.
It screws up all my arrangements.

1907
02:43:10,880 --> 02:43:12,142
Oh, that's what he said.

1908
02:43:12,186 --> 02:43:13,535
I can't go either, Sal.

1909
02:43:26,026 --> 02:43:30,030
Tell Mike it was only business.
I always liked him.

1910
02:43:31,727 --> 02:43:32,859
He understands that.

1911
02:43:32,902 --> 02:43:34,513
Excuse me, Sal.

1912
02:43:40,606 --> 02:43:43,043
Tom, can you get me
off the hook?

1913
02:43:44,218 --> 02:43:45,611
For old times' sake?

1914
02:43:45,654 --> 02:43:47,395
Can't do it, Sally.

1915
02:44:19,079 --> 02:44:20,733
[TELEPHONE BEING DIALED]

1916
02:44:32,701 --> 02:44:34,964
You have to answer
for Santino, Carlo.

1917
02:44:40,622 --> 02:44:42,189
Mike, you got it
all wrong.

1918
02:44:42,232 --> 02:44:45,627
You fingered Sonny
for Barzini.

1919
02:44:45,671 --> 02:44:49,370
That little farce you
played with my sister.

1920
02:44:49,413 --> 02:44:51,285
You think that could fool
a Corleone?

1921
02:44:51,328 --> 02:44:54,723
Mike, I'm innocent.
I swear on the kids, Mike.

1922
02:44:54,767 --> 02:44:56,682
Please, Mike, don't do this.
Sit down.

1923
02:45:00,163 --> 02:45:02,470
Don't do this
to me, please.

1924
02:45:11,566 --> 02:45:13,437
Barzini is dead.

1925
02:45:15,265 --> 02:45:17,398
So is Philip Tattaglia.

1926
02:45:18,878 --> 02:45:20,183
Moe Greene.

1927
02:45:21,402 --> 02:45:25,319
Strachi. Cuneo.

1928
02:45:27,103 --> 02:45:28,888
Today I settle
all family business,

1929
02:45:28,931 --> 02:45:32,456
so don't tell me
you're innocent, Carlo.

1930
02:45:32,500 --> 02:45:34,502
Admit what you did.

1931
02:45:38,114 --> 02:45:39,855
Get him a drink.

1932
02:45:46,122 --> 02:45:47,428
Come on.

1933
02:45:48,777 --> 02:45:51,258
Don't be afraid, Carlo.

1934
02:45:51,301 --> 02:45:55,088
Come on. Do you think I'd
make my sister a widow?

1935
02:45:55,131 --> 02:45:57,873
I'm godfather
to your son, Carlo.

1936
02:46:04,793 --> 02:46:06,795
Go ahead, drink, drink.

1937
02:46:11,800 --> 02:46:16,675
No, Carlo, you're out of the family
business. That's your punishment.

1938
02:46:16,718 --> 02:46:20,722
You're finished.
I'm putting you on a plane to Vegas.

1939
02:46:20,766 --> 02:46:22,332
Tom.

1940
02:46:26,510 --> 02:46:29,035
I want you to stay there.
Understand?

1941
02:46:29,078 --> 02:46:30,340
Mmm-hmm.

1942
02:46:30,384 --> 02:46:33,996
Only don't tell me
you're innocent.

1943
02:46:34,040 --> 02:46:38,261
Because it insults my intelligence.
Makes me very angry.

1944
02:46:42,570 --> 02:46:44,616
Who approached you?

1945
02:46:45,704 --> 02:46:48,097
Tattaglia or Barzini?

1946
02:46:56,018 --> 02:46:57,672
It was Barzini.

1947
02:47:01,850 --> 02:47:03,417
Good.

1948
02:47:09,684 --> 02:47:13,775
There's a car waiting outside
to take you to the airport.

1949
02:47:13,819 --> 02:47:16,430
I'll call your wife and tell
her what flight you're on.

1950
02:47:21,653 --> 02:47:24,133
Mike...
Come on, get out of my sight.

1951
02:47:50,159 --> 02:47:51,987
Hello, Carlo.

1952
02:47:55,208 --> 02:47:56,688
[GRUNTING]

1953
02:48:50,219 --> 02:48:51,438
[CONNIE SCREAMING]

1954
02:48:51,481 --> 02:48:52,744
I'm trying
to tell you...

1955
02:48:52,787 --> 02:48:55,007
CONNIE: Oh, Mama, please!

1956
02:49:00,360 --> 02:49:01,578
[SOBBING]

1957
02:49:03,232 --> 02:49:05,365
Michael! Michael!

1958
02:49:05,408 --> 02:49:07,628
KAY: What is it?
CONNIE: Where is he?

1959
02:49:10,109 --> 02:49:15,027
Michael, you lousy bastard!
You killed my husband.

1960
02:49:15,070 --> 02:49:19,205
You waited until Papa died, so nobody
could stop you and then you killed him.

1961
02:49:19,248 --> 02:49:22,338
You blamed him for Sonny.
You always did. Everybody did.

1962
02:49:22,382 --> 02:49:26,125
But you never thought about me!
You never gave a damn about me!

1963
02:49:26,168 --> 02:49:28,170
Now what are we gonna do?

1964
02:49:28,214 --> 02:49:30,042
KAY: Connie.

1965
02:49:32,305 --> 02:49:35,003
CONNIE: Why do you think
he kept Carlo at the Mall?

1966
02:49:35,047 --> 02:49:37,789
All the time he knew
he was going to kill him.

1967
02:49:37,832 --> 02:49:40,661
And you stood godfather
to our baby.

1968
02:49:40,704 --> 02:49:43,229
You lousy
cold-hearted bastard!

1969
02:49:43,272 --> 02:49:45,448
Want to know how many men
he had killed with Carlo?

1970
02:49:45,492 --> 02:49:47,320
Read the papers,
read the papers!

1971
02:49:47,363 --> 02:49:50,149
That's your husband,
that's your husband!

1972
02:49:52,368 --> 02:49:53,674
[CONNIE SPITTING]

1973
02:49:57,634 --> 02:49:59,288
[CONNIE SOBBING]

1974
02:49:59,854 --> 02:50:04,076
No! No, no...

1975
02:50:04,119 --> 02:50:07,470
Take her upstairs.
Get her a doctor.

1976
02:50:11,213 --> 02:50:12,693
[MICHAEL SIGHS]

1977
02:50:28,404 --> 02:50:30,102
She's hysterical.

1978
02:50:34,933 --> 02:50:36,630
Hysterical.

1979
02:50:38,588 --> 02:50:39,720
Michael, is it true?

1980
02:50:42,331 --> 02:50:44,377
Don't ask me
about my business, Kay.

1981
02:50:44,420 --> 02:50:46,161
Is it true?

1982
02:50:46,205 --> 02:50:47,771
Don't ask me
about my business.

1983
02:50:47,815 --> 02:50:49,295
No.
Enough!

1984
02:51:09,010 --> 02:51:10,533
All right.

1985
02:51:13,319 --> 02:51:15,060
This one time.

1986
02:51:19,151 --> 02:51:21,283
This one time I'll let you
ask me about my affairs.

1987
02:51:28,464 --> 02:51:29,901
Is it true?

1988
02:51:33,992 --> 02:51:35,471
Is it?

1989
02:51:36,995 --> 02:51:38,387
No.

1990
02:51:52,532 --> 02:51:55,535
I guess we both need a drink.
Come on.

1991
02:52:07,764 --> 02:52:09,201
[GLASS CLINKING]

1992
02:52:26,653 --> 02:52:28,350
Don Corleone.

